title: raisin pie
directions: Rinse raisins; drain.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler.
Set over simmering water.
Add water gradually, stirring constantly.
Stir in raisins.
Bring to boil; stir constantly and cook about 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat. Add small amount of hot mixture to egg, then stir egg into mixture in double boiler.
Return to heat and cook over simmering water about 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon peel and juice; cool.
Pour mixture into 9-inch pie pan; crisscross with narrow pastry strips from remaining dough.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes longer or until done.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix until thick and smooth.
Pour onto cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
When cake is done, flip onto a tea towel.
Remove wax paper.
Roll up and cool completely.

title: beef and potato bake
directions: Combine carrots, potatoes, onion, bell pepper, 3/4 teaspoon salt and first 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add 1/2 of the soup, bread crumbs (oats) and the other salt and pepper.
Add meat.
Mix well. Form into a loaf.
Place atop vegetables.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Saute chopped onions and bell pepper in butter; add peeled shrimp and cook until pink.
Mix in soup and tomatoes; put into a large baking dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger casserole no. 2
directions: Saute onions and pepper, then put in hamburger and brown.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in preheated 425° oven and bake covered 1/2 hour and uncovered 1/2 hour.

title: frozen bananoids
directions: Cook chocolate and milk in top of double boiler until melted. Remove from heat.
Line two paper plates with waxed paper.
Cut each banana into thirds.
Using tongs, dip banana piece into melted chocolate to cover, then roll in nuts and/or coconut.
Set "Bananoids" on paper plates and put in freezer until set.

title: stroganoff
directions: Drain steaks and cut into 1/4-inch wide strips.
Brown strips in oil.
Add mushrooms and onion soup mix.
Heat to boiling.
Put the flour into the sour cream and blend.
Combine with first mixture.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: asparagus
directions: Spread crackers and butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with asparagus and chestnuts.
Combine oleo and flour.
Add milk and cheese.
Pour over asparagus.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: greek salad
directions: Proportions are to your discretion.

title: orange-cream fruit salad
directions: Combine fruits (except strawberries) in large bowl.
In small bowl combine dry pudding mix, milk and orange juice.
Beat until blended.
Beat in sour cream.
Fold into fruit mixture.
Gently stir in strawberries.
Cover and chill.
Serves 10.

title: ice cream pie spectacular
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients, stirring well.
Press mixture firmly into a buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Spoon coffee ice cream into pie crust; spread evenly.
Freeze until firm.
Spread vanilla ice cream on top; freeze again until firm.
Spoon warmed sauce of desired flavor over slices.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Put everything in a bowl, except the chocolate.
Beat for 5 minutes at medium speed.
Grate the chocolate squares; add to cake mixture, along with the chocolate chips.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Leave cake in pan for 30 minutes before turning over.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Fold in walnuts.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool thoroughly on wire racks.

title: tuna sandwich
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Fill buns with mixture.
Wrap in foil.
Heat in oven at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Mix sherbet into juice in a large container; pour ginger ale last.
Yield:
Serves 50 people.

title: quick and easy fruit cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk, oleo and vanilla.
Pour in baking dish and top with chopped fruit.
Bake in 325° oven until done (about 45 minutes).

title: mexican hominy
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add hominy and chilies.
Add soup and cheese or Cheez Whiz.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add potato chips and nuts.
Drop 1/2 to 3/4 teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Place angel food pieces in casserole (cover bottom).
Mix milk and instant pudding mix in a small bowl.
Mix Jell-O and water in separate bowl.
Mix pudding and Jell-O mixes together; add strawberries.
Pour over angel food cake.
Refrigerate for about 4 hours before serving.
When ready to serve, spread Cool Whip over cake.

title: grandma rachel hernandez' fish patties
directions: Put steaks in a large frying pan with 1 cup water to steam. Add salt and pepper to taste. Cook until fish turns white, about 20 to 25 minutes.
It should flake apart and crumble. Shred fish. Put in a large bowl to cool.
Pick out bones.
In another large bowl, put eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add cornmeal. Spray frying pan with Pam and oil; heat.
Plop 1 heaping serving spoonful and fry approximately 1 minute on each side or until golden brown.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and soda together.
Pour juice into 4-cup measuring cup.
Add rind and shortening and enough boiling water to make 3 cups of liquid.
Make well in the center of the dry ingredients.
Add liquid with orange rind.
Stir until dampened.
Add nuts and cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Bake in bread pans (6 small or 2 large).
Great at holiday time and for gifts.

title: baked fish with apricot sauce
directions: If
using frozen fish, thaw.
Cut into 6 equal portions and arrange
in
a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle fish with garlic salt; set aside.

title: creme de menthe dessert
directions: Crush cookies until fine.
Melt marshmallows in milk in top of double boiler; cool.
Add creme de menthe, food coloring and flavoring.
Fold in whipped cream; mix well.
Put half of cookie mixture in bottom of 9-inch cake pan.
Add mixture, cover with rest of cookies.
Freeze.
Keeps for several weeks.
Do not thaw before serving.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar.
Then add flour, cinnamon, salt and carrots.
Bake at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, butter and confectioners sugar.
Add vanilla and pecans.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Blend and mix 3 minutes; pour into greased 9 or 10-inch pie pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread and place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Brown and drain sausage.
Spoon sausage over bread.
Sprinkle cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cheese will rise to top.
May be made the night before, covered and refrigerated.

title: berry berry pie
directions: Mix berries, sugar and cornstarch; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with crust.
Slit top crust and top with butter. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely before slicing.
Any combination of berries can be used in this pie.
Just be sure to use frozen or fresh for both berries.

title: pineapple sherbet punch
directions: Chill juices and ginger ale.
Combine in punch bowl.
Float spoonful of slightly softened sherbet in punch bowl.

title: boiled custard
directions: Scald all but 1/2 pint cream (that means, put over heat and stir constantly until you see come up).
Mix eggs, sugar, flour and salt.
Pour into milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Let cook about 15 minutes.
Let cool and add vanilla.
Whip the cream and fold into other when it has cooled.
(This stuff can be drunk or put into ice cream freezer.
To drink it is better.)

title: tetrazzini supper
directions: Mix together mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and milk. Cook macaroni, drain and add oil.
Add meat, green pepper and olives.
Pour soup mixture over macaroni; top with cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Add almonds and bake 10 minutes more.
This may be put together and refrigerated 24 hours, then add 10 minutes more to the baking time.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until middle is set.

title: marinated spareribs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place ribs in pan.
Add slice of onion and cover with water.
Simmer for 50 minutes.
Drain and place ribs in an ovenproof baking dish and chill.
Mix the sugar, cornstarch, curry powder and cloves.
Add boiling water, vinegar, soy sauce and garlic.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and boiling.
Pour over ribs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put chicken in Dutch oven.
Cover with water.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 2 1/2 hours.
Prepare dumplings.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: You will also need Pam vegetable spray.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Stew chicken, cool and bone.
Steam broccoli until tender. Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Place chicken on bottom and broccoli on top.
Combine mayonnaise, soup, curry powder and lemon juice.
Pour over broccoli; sprinkle with mixture of cheese and bread crumbs combined with butter.
(I double the cheese, bread crumbs and butter.)
Do not use seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apple slices in a 9-inch buttered pan.
Mix flour, oats, sugar and cinnamon in a separate bowl.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Great with ice cream!

title: tomato supreme
directions: Wash and cut medium sized ripe tomatoes in half crosswise. Place on greased pan and cover with mixture of sour cream, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Or tomatoes are good diced and covered with heavy cream, salt and pepper and broiled.
Put on slice of onion and Cheddar cheese and broil.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer the ingredients in the order given in a large bowl or deep casserole.
Cover and seal edges with Hellmann's real mayonnaise (1 pint).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover thoroughly with Bac*Os.
Cover entire top of bowl with Saran Wrap. Let set 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour to a thick paste (about 10 minutes). Cream together the Crisco and sugar and add paste to it.
Mix until fluffy.
Fold in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken; cool and remove meat.
Cook broccoli and drain. Spread broccoli in bottom of dish.
Place cut up chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix together cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice for sauce and pour over chicken.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel chex
directions: Combine butter, corn syrup, brown sugar and salt in a large glass bowl.
Heat in microwave on High, stopping frequently to stir, until the mixture comes to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from the microwave and stir in baking soda.
Place Corn Chex in a large brown paper grocery bag.
Pour caramel mixture over cereal.
Stir, close bag and shake to coat the cereal.
Heat in microwave on High 2 minutes.
Remove and shake.
Heat in microwave another 2 minutes.
Remove and spread on cookie sheets or waxed paper to cool.

title: parmesan cream cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed until smooth.
Add mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Beat until blended.
Stir in crumbled bacon and green onions.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Shape into a ball; garnish, if desired.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: peach pie
directions: Cook 3 cups peaches and 1/4 cup sugar until mixture comes to a boil.
Add remaining sugar, butter, salt and cornstarch.
Cook until clear and glossy.
Place remaining peaches in cooked pastry shell.
Pour hot mixture over peaches.
Chill until cold.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: Boil sugar and Pet cream for 15 minutes.
Take off stove.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a buttered dish.
Cut when cool.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Wash and cut tomatoes into slices.
Slice onions thin.
Dice peppers and sprinkle with 3/4 cup salt.
Let stand overnight.

title: zesty italian chicken
directions: Marinate (completely covered) chicken breasts in Zesty Italian dressing for 3 hours.
May marinate for more or less time depending on how zesty you want them.

title: apple salad
directions: Chop apples; combine apples with remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: old fashioned sugar cream pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, cream and vanilla.
Fold white sugar and flour into beaten egg whites.
Fold white sugar mixture into brown sugar mixture.
Pour into your favorite 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes and then reduce heat to 325° for 30 to 50 minutes.
When done, it is firm to within 1/2-inch from center.

title: two-crust cherry pie
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar with cornstarch.
Stir in cherry juice. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Cool 1 minute longer.
Add remaining sugar, cherries, butter and food coloring.
(Mixture will be very thick.) Let stand while preparing pastry.
Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry; fill.
Adjust top crust, cutting slits for escape of steam; seal.
Bake at 400° for 55 minutes.

title: fudge balls
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler and let stand to cool.
When chocolate is cooled, fold in the whipped cream.
Let stand until cool and thick.
Form into balls and roll in ground nuts.

title: pineapple upside-down cake for two
directions: In an 8-inch iron skillet, combine butter and sugar.
Heat to melt until it comes to bubbling.
Drop pineapple into syrup you have taken off heat.
Then drop maraschino cherries in open spaces of pineapple slices.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine in a saucepan; bring to a boil, remove from heat, cool slightly and add vanilla.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat thoroughly.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; add to the creamed mixture and mix well.
Fold in oats and nut meats.
Drop from a teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes before removing from a cookie sheet. Makes about 5 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and add enough flour to make a soft bread dough.
Put in large bowl and cover with a towel. Put in a warm place and let rise until twice its size.
Put on a floured surface and knead again.
Put back in bowl, cover and let it rise to twice its size again.
Knead again and roll out to 1/2 inch thickness.

title: lemon building bars
directions: Mix; press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool to room temperature.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix together and place in crock-pot.
Slice a few slices of cheese and place on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook 4 hours on low heat.

title: fresh turnips(tops and roots)
directions: Clean and wash turnip tops thoroughly (3 or 4 washes).
After last wash, take small bunches of leaves at a time and chop into small chunks.
Place leaves in a large pot with about 1/2 quart water and whichever seasoning you choose (bacon, etc.).
Add salt and cook at least 1 hour.
If your turnips have roots, wash, peel and cut into pieces.
Add to cooking turnip tops and cook until tops and roots are tender.
Add water as needed.
Start cooking on high and lower to medium high when they come to a boil.
If you don't add roots, cook greens until tender.
Follow same recipe for rutabaga tops and roots.

title: easy pudding rolls
directions: Cut bread in one fourths.
Place in a tube pan.
Sprinkle with pudding, brown sugar and pecans.
Pour melted butter over all ingredients.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
You may use more sugar and butter if you want them sweeter.

title: megan's purple ribbon gingersnaps
directions: Lightly grease cookie sheets.
In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients; blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill dough for easier handling.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in sugar and place 2 inches apart on prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are set.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind apples, cranberries, oranges and nuts.
Mix jello in hot water and add sugar and all other ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm.
Keeps well and can be frozen.

title: bean burrito bake
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Mix the first 3 ingredients. Spread onto bottom and halfway up side of greased 10-inch deep pie plate. Add the next 3 ingredients in order.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and lined 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and place in pan. Cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheese-stuffed shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw spinach and squeeze out moisture. In a large bowl, mix next seven ingredients.
Fill each shell with 1/4 of cheese mixture.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples; cut in eighths.
Arrange in unbaked pie shell. Mix 1/2 cup sugar with the cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.

title: pineapple syrup
directions: Place pineapple and corn syrup in blender.
Blend at high speed for 10 seconds; refrigerate.
Use within 2 weeks.
Makes 1 1/2 cups of syrup.
Serve over ice cream.

title: flounder fillet
directions: Rinse fish fillet.
Reheat oven to 375°.
Coat the fish fillet in the rye flour.
Sprinkle both sides with the chives and seasoning.
Place in a glass baking dish.
Pour the lemon juice over the fish fillet.
Cover with the glass lid.
Place the dish in the heated oven for 20 minutes or until the fish falls apart while lifted with a fork.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Saute chicken in oil in a medium skillet (add a little water if necessary) until chicken is cooked through.
Add dried onions, Worcestershire sauce, chicken soup and water.
Simmer while preparing Stove Top dressing, following package directions.

title: pickled beans
directions: Boil together and pour over cooked string beans.
Seal while hot.

title: esta lawrence's pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, white sugar and oleo.
Blend together and add eggs and pumpkin.
Sift together and add the flour, soda, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add chopped walnuts and dates. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cocoa treats
directions: Melt cream and butter.
Stir in candy bar.
Pour over Rice Krispies.
Add marshmallows.
Spread in greased baking pan.

title: carter cookies
directions: Mix and drop on waxed paper to dry.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight (this is a must).
Serve with chips or fresh vegetables.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Beat eggs with hand. Add sugar, margarine, vanilla and nuts. Continue to stir with hand.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Pare and cut up sweet potatoes.
Place in saucepan and just cover with water.
Boil 30 minutes or until tender. Drain potatoes and mash with fork.
Add remaining ingredients, except marshmallows and pecans.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into greased casserole dish.
Cover with marshmallows and pecans.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: unique pretzels
directions: Measure warm water into large mixing bowl.
Sprinkle on yeast; stir until it looks soft.
Add sugar, salt and flour; mix and knead dough until soft and no longer sticky.
Take a small ball of dough the size of an egg.
Roll the dough between the palms of your hands or on the table top until it is as long as a snake. Twist the snake into a pretzel, letters, numbers or any shape. Grease cookie sheets.
Place twisted pretzels or designs on cookie sheets.
Brush pretzels with beaten egg; sprinkle with sesame seed or coarse salt.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden.
Let cool.

title: salsa dip
directions: Peel and cut tomatoes.
Remove most seeds from tomatoes.
Drain tomatoes.
Make enough tomatoes to make 1 gallon.
Put drained tomatoes and all other ingredients into a large pot and let it boil slowly for approximately 2 hours or until it reaches the consistency for easy dipping with tortilla chips, etc.
Salsa may be put into jars and sealed tightly.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: overnight salad
directions: Beat eggs in top of double boiler.
Add vinegar, sugar and butter.
Cook over boiling water, stirring until thick.
Cool. Fold in whipped cream, fruits and marshmallows.
Chill 24 hours. Serve in lettuce cups.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with eggs, then carrots and nuts.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for
60 to 65 minutes.

title: jelly roll delight
directions: Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with sliced jelly roll.
Mix vanilla pudding according to instruction.
Pour over jelly roll.
Add thick layer of preserves and top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle chopped nuts and sliced strawberries on top.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Spread 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish generously with butter. Roll chicken pieces that have been seasoned with salt and pepper, if desired, in Ritz cracker crumbs.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine all ingredients; spread a generous portion on individual Tostitos chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: mushroom swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Coat with combined flour, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in skillet and brown steak on both sides. Put steak in a shallow baking pan and top each piece with an onion slice.
Heat soup in skillet and pour over steak.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: eating wells chewy oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread rolled oats and nuts on an ungreased baking sheet and toast for 5 to 7 minutes or lightly browned; set aside.
Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper or coat with nonstick cooking spray.
In small saucepan combine raisins with 1 cup water. Bring to a simmer over low heat and cook until the raisins are plumped, about 10 minutes.
Drain, discarding liquid; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl beat sugar, apple butter, eggs, oil and vanilla with an electric mixer until light and fluffy, about 5 minutes.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and cloves into another bowl.
Stir the flour mixture into the apple butter mixture with a spoon. Stir in the reserved oats, nuts and raisins; mix well.
Drop the dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto the prepared baking sheets.
Bake, one sheet at a time, for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Transfer cookies to racks and let cool.
Calories 114, fat 3.

title: mystery cookies
directions: Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine vanilla and eggs and stir into dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add butter and mix until smooth.
Add nuts.

title: "cajun" new orleans cooking school jambalaya
directions: Saute sausage, paprika and cayenne for several minutes.
Add onions, pepper and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add bay leaves and thyme.
Add rice.
Stir until coated in oil.
Add tomatoes, chicken broth, garlic, kielbasa (sliced like quarters) and ham. Bring mixture to boil.
Cover; let simmer 30 minutes until rice is done.
Before serving, remove bay leaf.
Add green onions and parsley.
Serve hot with French bread and green salad.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in a huge bowl and mash, knead and squeeze.
Form into small balls, midway between filbert and walnut sizes, and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Butter bottom of a small glass; dip it in granulated sugar and mash balls flat.
Keep doing it.
(You need butter the glass only once or twice but re-dip it in sugar for each ball.)
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 15 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Top with cracker or bread crumbs and butter. Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Melt margarine in a small saucepan over medium heat.
Add cocoa.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture just begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour into a small mixer bowl; cool completely.
Add powdered sugar, alternately with milk, beating to spreading consistency.
Blend in vanilla.
Makes 2 cups frosting.

title: turkey noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Stir cooked noodles with remaining ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper.
Heat oven to 350° and bake in 3-quart covered casserole for approximately 45 minutes.

title: baked creole eggplant
directions: Boil eggplants until soft.
Saute onion, shrimp and celery in butter.
Combine with eggplant.
Put in baking pan and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add egg yolk and cream; beat constantly while adding cheese a tablespoon at a time.
Put drained noodles in large heated serving bowl.
Add cheese mixture to noodles.
Prepare just before serving as it should be served immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: just for kids halloween party cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; with grown-up help.
Place paper liners in 24 muffin pans.
Fill cups 3/4 full.
Bake and cool cupcakes following package directions.
Frost with chocolate frosting and decorate with candies.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Drain dill pickles (reserve juice).
Slice lengthwise or in chips.
Use glass or enamel bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let stand at room temperature for 4 hours, stirring occasionally. Pack in container and refrigerate.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread on flour tortillas.
Roll up each and secure with toothpicks.
Chill 8 hours or overnight.
Slice into 1-inch sections.
Serve with picante sauce.
Slices best with electric knife.

title: mom's sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into tube pan, wax paper lined on bottom, and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: avocado crunchies
directions: Peel, seed and mash ripe avocado with lemon juice.
Blend until smooth and add dill and pepper sauce.
Carefully spread on chips and garnish with a slice of green olive.
Serve immediately as appetizers.

title: sin cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, 1 egg and oleo or butter with pecans.
Press in an 11 x 13-inch greased and floured pan; set aside.
Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese and sugar together; pour over first mixture. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, or until top is golden brown.

title: easy turkey divan
directions: Wash broccoli.
Remove tough part of stalk.
Cut stalks lengthwise into quarters.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Place in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover with turkey.
Combine soup, water, mayonnaise, lemon juice and seasonings.
Pour over turkey.
Mix butter, crumbs and cheese.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef or turkey well; drain and add tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Cook until well blended.
Toss all ingredients together.
Add dressing right before serving.

title: ham 'n tater bake
directions: Arrange potatoes in a layer on bottom and up sides of 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat in oven at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes until potatoes are lightly browned.
Reduce oven to 350°.
While potatoes are baking, combine soup and milk over low heat.
Stir until blended, then add ham.
Stir in thawed broccoli and turn mixture into casserole over potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until cheese is melted and mixture is bubbly. Serves 6.

title: pepper and rice timbales
directions: In a medium pan, combine water and bouillon granules.
Bring to boiling.
Add uncooked rice.
Return to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in chopped pepper.
Cover and let stand for 10 minutes.
For each timbale, spray one 5 ounce custard cup.
Immediately pack the rice mixture into the cup.
Invert onto a serving plate.
Remove cup.

title: salami fettucine pasta
directions: In skillet, add oil and garlic.
Cook about 3 to 4 minutes and then add zucchini and salami, stirring until zucchini is almost done.
(Do not overcook zucchini.)
Add cream, capers, salt and pepper.
Serve over pasta at once. Serves 4.

title: potato-topped cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in shortening; drain. Add salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, corn, cheese and catsup; mix well. Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole dish. Blend egg yolk and potatoes; spread over meat mixture or spoon around edge. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. For more crisp topping, place under broiler for several minutes.

title: wholemeal carrot and apple scones(makes 8)
directions: Heat oven to gas mark 6, 400°F or 200°C.

title: cheese balls
directions: Blend well the cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except pecans.
Chill 2 hours.
Divide cheese in half and shape in 2 balls.
Roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: pig-licking cake
directions: Mix all ingredients 3 minutes.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch sheet pan in a 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with the following Frosting recipe.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Add water and yeast together until yeast is dissolved.
Add cake mix and enough flour to make stiff dough.
Knead, let rise until double in size.
Roll out.
Add brown sugar, cinnamon, nuts and raisins (optional).
Roll up slice about 1 to 1 1/2-inch slices.
Place in buttered pan and let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° until golden brown and glaze.

title: eggplant creole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Cook eggplant for 10 minutes in boiling water; drain.
Place in greased casserole.
Add flour to butter and stir until blended.
Add tomatoes, green pepper and onion to butter mixture with salt.
Cook ingredients 5 minutes, stirring until thickened.
Pour over eggplant.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Dot lightly with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Prepare brownie mix and pudding according to package directions, except don't chill pudding.
Layer half each brownie, pudding topping, toffee and nuts.
Repeat layers.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: chile con queso dip
directions: Heat all ingredients over low heat, stirring constantly, until all the cheese has melted.
Serve with tortilla chips or your favorite chips.

title: sauce for meatballs
directions: Bring to boil; simmer 10 minutes.
Place meatballs in bowl and pour sauce over them.
Let marinate a few hours or overnight. Heat 45 minutes.
Add to sauce 1 can chunk pineapple and 1/2 cup pineapple sauce.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Beat eggs smooth.
Add buttermilk; mix well.
Add sugar, flour, butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: classic beef bouillon
directions: Crack the bones.
Brown them in a small amount of fat in a large kettle.
Add everything else.
Bring to a boil and skim off the foam.
Simmer, covered, for 3 hours until the broth is reduced by half.
Take out the bones and the large pieces of meat and vegetables.
Strain the broth through a cheesecloth.
Use in any recipe calling for beef bouillon or serve as a clear soup.

title: tropical kumquat cake
directions: In a bowl beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Fold in dry ingredients, and nuts.
Add kumquats, and pineapple.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in 350° oven. Cool; remove from pan.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix and cook until thick.
Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: deviled ham balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and roll into 25 small balls. Freeze for 30 minutes.
Take balls from the freezer and roll in the softened cream cheese. Either roll in chives or nuts. Chill until ready to serve. Serve on toothpicks.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix together the vanilla wafers, granulated sugar and chopped nuts.
Add melted butter and rum.
Roll into balls and then roll in powdered sugar.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Blend and chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish with water to cover bottom. (You may brown pork chops under broiler first, but not necessary.) On each pork chop, squeeze lemon juice, then spread catsup and sprinkle brown sugar.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: carrots and mushrooms
directions: Slice carrots diagonally into thin slices.
Combine butter, oil, onion and garlic in skillet and saute for 1 minute.
Add carrots, mushrooms and seasonings.
Simmer, covered, over low heat for 15 minutes or until carrots are crisp-tender.
Serve hot.

title: tomato cream soup
directions: Strain tomatoes through a strainer.
Place over medium heat and heat through.
Add baking soda.
When juice ceases to foam, add milk, butter, salt and pepper.

title: boiled fish
directions: Use a two-gallon pot.
Fill 3/4 full of water.
Add two large potatoes and about 1/2 cup salt.
Bring water to boil.
Add a fatty fish such as trout.
Cook until done (fork easily penetrates flesh).
Season and serve.
Larger fish are best prepared by this method.
Allow 2 lb. fish for every 2 potatoes.

title: lizzies
directions: Mix cut cherries, pineapple, pecans, and raisins and dredge all in flour.
(This flour is not included in the 6 cups.)
Mix 5 cups of the flour with cinnamon, soda, cloves, nutmeg, and all spice and sift once.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add bourbon and milk and mix.
Then add dry ingredients and mix.
Add fruits and nuts.
Work well with hands so fruit is well mixed.
Add the other cup of flour if needed to help stick together.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until golden brown. Pack in airtight container with waxed paper between layers. Let cookies cure 3-4 weeks to develop flavor.
Makes 350-400 cookies.

title: chew bread
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, then well beaten eggs.
Add flour and vanilla.
Then stir in nuts.
Bake in an 8 x 12-inch greased pan at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pour 1/2 to 1 cup water in a 9 x 9-inch pan and add vanilla. Add enough sliced apples so pan is about 3/4 full.
Sprinkle apples with cinnamon.

title: creole of shrimp
directions: Cook and clean shrimp.
Melt butter in large skillet over low heat.
Add separate onion rings and green pepper slices and cook until onion is tender.
Sprinkle flour over vegetables in skillet and brown golden.
Stir in tomatoes.
Season.
Cook slowly about 10 minutes; add shrimp.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Heat milk.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Mix sugar, cocoa and flour. Add to milk mixture, stirring vigorously.
Return to heat and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla. Cool and pour into pie shell.
Cover with meringue.
Bake in slow oven, 300°, until brown.

title: apricot nut tea bread
directions: Soak apricots for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, cream together 1 cup sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in 1/4 cup sugar and orange juice.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Drain apricots and stir into mixture.
Add nuts and stir.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Wrap tightly to freeze.
Freezes nicely.
A moist bread that is better if eaten a day after it is baked.
Serves 12.

title: cherry apple upside-down cake
directions: Spread apples evenly into a 9 x 13-inch sprayed pan.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon evenly over apples.
Then put cherry pie filling over the apples.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and cottage cheese.
Add Cool Whip and mix well. Add well drained pineapple; mix well.
Refrigerate and it's ready to eat.

title: meat loaf wellington
directions: You will need 1 large sheet of wax paper.

title: salt and alum modeling clay
directions: Add a small amount of water to the dry ingredients to form clay.

title: galumki(pigs in a blanket)
directions: Cook rice; set aside to cool.

title: sky-high biscuits
directions: Combine all dry ingredients. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add egg and milk, stirring quickly and briefly.
Knead lightly on a floured board.
Pat gently to 1-inch thickness.
Cut into 1 to 2-inch biscuits.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Generously butter a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, toss potatoes with 1/2 cup of the Gruyere cheese and flour.
Arrange potatoes in three layers, seasoning with salt and pepper and sprinkling remaining 3/4 cup Gruyere and bits of butter between layers and on top.
Pour chicken stock over top.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours until potatoes are tender and golden brown on top.

title: squash fritters
directions: Grate squash and onion to a 75/25 mix squash to onion by volume.
Add egg and flour as needed to make them stick together in patties.

title: easy chicken stir-fry
directions: Cook and stir chicken breast, cut into strips; add garlic in hot oil in large skillet.
On medium-high heat chicken is cooked through.
Add water, stir fry, kikkoman sauce and sugar.
Stir; bring to boil.
Stir in uncooked rice, cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.

title: beef beans and rice
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain fat from meat.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a casserole dish and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and mushroom gravy
directions: Salt and fry chicken pieces until golden brown and well done. Add soup and water.
Reduce heat to simmer, stirring often.
Let simmer approximately 35 minutes or until gravy is golden brown.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into a greased pan. Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: greek chicken
directions: Wash fryer well; season inside and out with salt, pepper, oregano and lemon juice (must use fresh lemons) and garlic.
Brush with olive oil; dot with butter over breast and legs.
Mix water with paste.
Place chicken in pan and drip tomato mixture over chicken.
Cover and bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Lower to 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Baste often.

title: honey-glazed carrots
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring carrots, honey and 1 cup water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover with lid slightly ajar and simmer until water is evaporated and carrots are tender, stirring occasionally.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: barbecue hamburgers
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add rest of the ingredients with 1/2 cup water.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: bean pot
directions: Brown beef, onions and green peppers and drain.
Place all ingredients in large pot and simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Stir very carefully as to not mash beans.
Delicious with cornbread.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan saute onion and green pepper in butter or margarine.
Stir in tomato ketchup, brown sugar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Use as a basting sauce during last 10 minutes of cooking.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: cranberry-orange muffins(or bread)
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together in a large mixing bowl. Then add remaining ingredients, folding together carefully.
Bake in muffin pan at 325°
about 20 to 25 minutes; for bread, 60 minutes or so.

title: congo bars
directions: Cream oleo and brown sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and soda.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in 13 x 9-inch or larger pan, depending on desired thickness.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; add pineapple, bananas, strawberries and nuts.
Divide mixture in half and let congeal.
Put cream in middle and pour on other half.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Place a large pan (Dutch oven type) 3/4 full of water on stove.
Heat to boiling.
Add the spaghetti; return to boil. Cover.
Remove from heat.

title: blintz souffle
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sour cream, orange juice, sugar, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place blintzes (seam side down) in pan.
Pour cooled mixture over layer of blintzes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Should be golden brown on top.

title: bite size fruitcake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Add fruit, raisins and pecans.
Pour milk over all ingredients; mix well.
Roll into bite size balls. Roll each ball in coconut.
Makes about 6 dozen.
These can be frozen.

title: cheese manicotti with meat sauce
directions: Mix
all
together. Cook 1 box manicotti as directed on box, then fill each one with cheese filling.

title: autumn soup
directions: *One can (28 ounces), with liquid can be substituted for the fresh tomatoes.
Reduce water to 3 cups.
Stir in tomatoes with the remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
The canned tomatoes break apart and give a rosy color.

title: sugar-free apple cobbler
directions: Mix apples, lemon juice, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.
Pour mixture into a nonstick 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand for 10 minutes.
Invert.
Sprinkle with sweetener (can also use cinnamon).
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 8 servings.

title: butter beans with bacon and green onion
directions: Cook butter beans according to package directions and set aside. Cook bacon in a large skillet over medium-high heat until crisp. Remove bacon, reserving drippings in skillet. Crumble bacon and set aside. Cook green onions and garlic in bacon drippings, stirring often. Stir in beans, parsley, salt and pepper. Cook just until heated. Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.

title: tomato refrigerator jam
directions: Boil pulp and sugar about 12 minutes. Take from stove and add jello and stir well until jello dissolves. Put in jars and keep refrigerated. Freezes well.

title: caramelized onion tart
directions: Cook onions in hot oil in a large skillet over low heat, stirring often, 30 to 35 minutes or until onion is caramel. Stir in salt and set mixture aside. Unfold pastry; fit into a 9-inch square tart pan. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned. Remove from oven. Press pastry with the back of a spoon to flatten. Top with caramelized onions. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake 5 more minutes.

title: pickle relish
directions: Put all vegetables through fine blade of meat grinder. Sprinkle with salt and let stand for 2 hours.
Drain well, adding all vegetables.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: cajun casserole, texas style
directions: Cook sausage.
Drain on paper towel and when cool to touch, cut into 1/2-inch diagonal slices.
Set aside.
Using a large Dutch oven, spray bottom with Pam (or coat bottom with olive oil) and add Spanish onion, garlic, rice, green onions, celery, green and red peppers.
Cook, stirring, until onion and celery are limp.
Add rest of ingredients except seafood.
Raise heat to high; bring to a boil and cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Then cover the pot, lower the heat to low and cook 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes approximately.

title: corned beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute cabbage, celery and onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake 45 to 50 minutes or until well heated.
Makes 8 servings.

title: no-bake pumpkin pie
directions: In a heavy medium saucepan, combine unflavored gelatin, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Let stand 1 minute.
Over low heat, cook and stir constantly until gelatin dissolves and mixture thickens slightly, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pumpkin; mix well.
Pour into a prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 1 pie.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Heat oil in heavy saucepan.
Stir in flour; cook until lightly browned.
Gradually stir in broth; set aside.
Saute bacon in soup kettle until crisp.
Add onions, garlic, green pepper, okra and tomatoes.
Cover; cook, stirring occasionally, until onions are golden.
Stir liquids into vegetable mixture.
Add all seasonings. Bring to a boil; cover and simmer for 2 hours.
About 30 minutes before serving, add seafood and salt if necessary.
Cook slowly, adding file powder right before removing from heat.
Serve on mound of rice.
May be prepared up to adding seafood and frozen. Serves 8.

title: banana pudding
directions: Using deep bowl, crumble a layer of vanilla wafers in bottom. Slice bananas over wafers and continue until bowl is half full. Mix Jell-O pudding mix with milk.
Beat with mixer about 2 minutes. Add can of Eagle Brand milk and 1/2 box of Cool Whip.
Mix good with mixer (2 minutes).
Pour half of mixture over layer of wafers and bananas.
Make another layer of wafers and bananas and pour remaining mixture over this layer.
Top with Cool Whip and put wafers around rim of bowl.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Mix together oil, sugar, vinegar and seasoning packets from Ramen noodles.
Stir in broken noodles.
Add onion, celery and broccoli slaw.
Stir.
Cover and refrigerate 12 hours.
Before serving add sunflower seeds and stir.

title: corn bread stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine biscuit crumbs and soft corn bread in a large bowl, then add chopped onion, diced celery, salt and pepper; mix all dry ingredients together.
Next, add 1/4 cup of water.
Stir all ingredients together; put in sugar and eggs. Mix until soft blended.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: honey-peanut cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter and honey.
Add eggs; mix well. Combine flour, sugar, soda, baking powder and salt; add to peanut butter mixture and mix well.

title: yellow punch
directions: Use proper liquid for frozen juices and jello.
Mix well and store in freezer.
To serve, thaw until slushy.
Add ginger ale before serving.
Serves 40-50 people.

title: pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper 6 pork chops on both sides to fit taste. Brown on both sides in frying pan. Put in a large pan with potatoes and carrots.
Heat oven to 350°, cook for 2 hours or until done.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry hamburg. Add chili powder.
Drain well.
Shred up lettuce. Slice tomatoes and chop black olives. Combine all ingredients except nacho chips and Catalina dressing.
Just before serving, crumble and add nacho chips. Toss salad and top with Catalina salad dressing. Sprinkle with chili powder.
Preparation time:
30 minutes.

title: mexican salad dip
directions: Layer bean dip in bottom of dish.
Mash avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Layer on top of bean dip.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning; layer on top of avocado.
Layer remaining ingredients one on top of the other.
Chill and serve with chips.

title: apple rolls
directions: Roll dough into a rectangle shape.
Spread with butter. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
(Cover the dough with the cinnamon and sugar.)
Sprinkle with chopped apples.
Use your own judgment on how much apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and cut into 1/2 to 1-inch slices.
Place in pan.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream butter and 1/4 cup confectioners sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour.
Add pecans; mix well.
Shape by 2 tablespoonfuls into 3-inch fingers on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Roll warm cookies in remaining 1/4 cup confectioners sugar.
Cool on wire rack completely.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: sweet lei-lanicake(banana pineapple)
directions: Wash and core as many apples as you need.
Set apples in buttered pie dish.
In each apple center, put in 1 level teaspoon cinnamon, a dash of nutmeg and fill to overflowing with honey. Bake at 400° until tender.

title: easy slaw dressing
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, salt, sugar and pepper.
Add vinegar and milk.
Whip with a wire whisk until sugar is dissolved.
This is enough dressing for 1/2 head cabbage.

title: vegetable beef barley soup
directions: Brown cubed meat in hot fat.
Place meat, water and seasonings in soup kettle.
Cook with cover slowly for 1 hour.
Add barley; cook another hour.
Cool and skim off excess fat.
Puree tomatoes. Add carrots, celery, onion, tomatoes and string beans.
Cook 45 minutes.
Best if made over 2 days.
Throw in 2 beef bouillon cubes if short on meat.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook onion in butter in a large skillet over medium heat until transparent.
Add beef and cook until brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper, mushrooms and soup.
Mix well.
Cool 5 minutes and add sour cream; stir well.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles. Garnish with paprika (optional).

title: onion casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 9-inch baking dish with Pam.
Slice onion.
Place in bottom of dish with slivered water chestnuts.
Add Total and almonds.
Pour margarine evenly over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake at 350°. Makes 3 layers.

title: tamale joe
directions: Brown sausage slowly in skillet and pour off fat.
Add beef and onion; cook and stir until meat loses red color.
Add seasonings, milk, corn and tomato sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes. Gradually stir corn meal into meat mixture.
Add olives.
Pour into 3-quart casserole and top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sugar and spiced nuts
directions: Put pecans in a large bowl. Put in unbeaten egg white.
Mix well with spoon until all halves are coated with egg white.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt, then sprinkle over mixture.
Mix well again.
Pour on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: bacon smokies
directions: Cut bacon strips into fourths.
Wrap each piece around one smokie.
Secure each with toothpick.
Place all on nonstick baking sheet.
Cover with brown sugar and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar. Bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a large baking sheet.
Cream shortening and sugars together in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, chocolate morsels and pecans.
Drop dough by level tablespoonful 2 inches apart onto prepared baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire racks. Makes about 70 cookies.

title: baked egg casserole
directions: Tear bread into chunks and put into greased casserole.
Melt butter.
Pour over bread. Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat the rest of the ingredients together.
Pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and brown.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift together plain flour, baking powder, salt and soda. Mix both together.
Fold in Rice Krispies and oatmeal.
Bake at 350°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove from broth, debone and dice.
Add sufficient water to chicken broth to cook spaghetti until just tender.
Drain spaghetti.
Mix warm spaghetti with cheese whiz and all other ingredients until blended.
Place in a 3-quart, greased casserole and warm in a 350° oven for about 25 minutes.

title: icebox yeast rolls
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Add 1 cup hot water.
Let cool and add eggs.
Mix.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of tepid water. Add to shortening mixture.
Add flour mixture to shortening stir well, cover and refrigerate over night.
Roll dough out on floured board, and cut with biscuit cutter.
Dab butter on each roll and rise 2 hours.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with mayonnaise. Stir in 1/2 cup sliced olives, the olive juice and pepper. Mix well. Refrigerate.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Grate onions, pickles and olives.
Mix and beat.
Chill for at least 30 minutes.

title: grilled corn on the cob
directions: Pull back small amount of husk.
Put small amount of butter on corn.
Put husks back over again.
Wrap in foil.
Put on hot grill, turning once in a while.
Leave on grill 15 to 30 minutes. Corn won't burn too fast.
Be careful, very hot when husking corn.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Blend all together in blender and use in favorite recipe when you are all out of Eagle Brand.

title: microwave fudge(great for kids)
directions: In a meat loaf pan, mix powdered sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Cook in microwave oven 3 1/2 minutes on High.
Remove and add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in square dish until it hardens. Children especially like to make this!

title: white chocolate cheese cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and sugar in large bowl.
Press into bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan. Refrigerate.

title: rigatoni with pesto(serves 8)
directions: Cook rigatoni as directed on package; drain.
Prepare Pesto Sauce (recipe follows); pour over rigatoni.
Toss until well coated.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: chocolate praline pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended. Stir in chocolate morsels and pecans.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Combine butter, salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Mix and add potatoes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Layer with corn flakes and butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat bananas on medium speed.
Add sugar, Crisco, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ray's ultimate barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ketchup with mustard first in a separate bowl. (Mustard will lump if added to mixture alone.)
Stir in black and red pepper until completely mixed, set aside. Slowly dissolve cornstarch in chilled spring water and set aside.

title: scalloped squash
directions: Cook squash until soft (I peel and cut into quarters and cut out seeds).
Add egg, butter, onion and seasonings to mashed squash and mix well.
Add cream and bread crumbs and bake at 375° until brown (I use a long Pyrex dish).

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Blend in egg.
Stir together the flour and salt; stir into the creamed mixture. Chill for 1 hour.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Flatten with a fork and top with pecan half.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: french onion soup
directions: Slice onions 1/8-inch thick.
Melt butter; place onions in it, saute slowly for 1 1/2 hours in a large soup pot.	Add all
other ingredients except bouillon, saute over low heat 10 minutes
more. Add
bouillon
and simmer for 2 hours.
Adjust color
to
a
rich brown with caramel coloring or Kitchen Bouquet.
Season
with salt to taste.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Yields 2 quarts finished soup.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and milk together.
Pour in pie shell.
Top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch dish, combine cooked rice, soup and 3/4 can of water.
Take bones out of chicken.
Lay chicken on rice.
Mix stuffing with broth and seasoning until moist.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers into bowl large enough to toss sliced cucumbers in.
Slice onion and separate into rings; then place in bowl with cucumbers.
Sprinkle with salt and toss.
Refrigerate for approximately 1/2 hour.
Remove from refrigerator and toss again. There should be juice from the cucumbers now in bottom of bowl.
If not, toss more vigorously and add a pinch more salt.
Refrigerate again for 1/2 hour.
If it still has not produced natural juices from the cucumbers, when tossing them, squeeze them slightly.
The juice should cover the bottom of the bowl.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook and drain ground meat;
season with garlic powder, onion salt
and
pepper.	Pour
beans into blender with water; blend. Pour into saucepan and heat.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Tear or cut into small pieces.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together and pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
If you like, Parmesan cheese may be shaken over the top of the casserole just before serving.

title: peach cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well a heavy 9-inch skillet. Cream butter and sugar until light.
Beat in egg.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat half into creamed mixture; beat in half of the milk.
Repeat, beating well.
Pour batter into prepared skillet.
Arrange peach slices on top of batter.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: red rice
directions: Fry bacon and break into pieces.
Chop onion fine.
(Be sure lumps are out of rice.)
Mix everything and put in greased dish. Cover and bake in moderate oven until onion is done.
Stir with fork several times while baking.

title: chicken delight
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Cut or tear into pieces.
Add water chestnuts to chicken, then soup, mayonnaise and celery.
Mix all together.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together the sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar.
Pour over remaining ingredients and stir.

title: chicken scallopini
directions: Dip chicken breast in flour, then into egg, then into bread crumbs.
Heat saute pan to medium heat and melt butter or margarine.
Place chicken in pan and cook each side 2 minutes, then add mushrooms and Chablis.
Cover and simmer 7 minutes or until done.
Serve atop rice or pasta, then pour any remaining wine/butter mixture and mushrooms on top.

title: fruit fluff
directions: Combine Bisquick, 3 tablespoons sugar; cut in butter.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes; cool.
Mix softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream and marshmallows.
Spread over crust.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours. Cut into squares and top with fresh fruit.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Combine pecans and coconut and sprinkle into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake according to box.
Pour cake mixture over pecan mixture.
Blend margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread on top of cake batter.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Cook onions until soft in hot oil.
Add all other ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour on chicken and cook in covered roaster 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Remove lid, if desired, to thicken sauce.

title: dog food
directions: Melt oleo, peanut butter and chocolate chips in large pan. Stir in cereal.
Cool.
Put powdered sugar in a brown paper bag. Add cereal mixture and shake until cereal is all coated.
Buy a new dog bowl and put cereal mix in it.

title: pea and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; chop up into smaller pieces.
Add peas; stir together.
Combine soup and Cheez Whiz in small bowl; microwave until the cheese is melted.
Stir the cheese until it is spread out with the soup.
Add to broccoli and peas; mix well.
Mix butter and cornbread mix; sprinkle over top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cool ranch crackers
directions: Mix oil, dill weed and dressing together in large sealable mixing bowl. Add crackers; seal and shake to coat crackers. Place crackers on a cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 20 minutes at 150°. Cool. Keep sealed in airtight container.

title: reese cups
directions: Work sugar, butter and margarine together with hands.
Form into small balls.
Melt in double boiler the paraffin and chocolate chips.
Keep warm in double boiler.
Dip balls into the mixture and lay on wax paper to dry.

title: six week muffins
directions: Put cereal in large bowl; add milk and let set 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add to cereal
gradually until all is mixed.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: german potato salad #1
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and crumble.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of drippings.
Cook onion in reserved drippings until tender.
Add sugar, flour, salt, beef bouillon, celery seed, allspice and the pepper.
Stir until the mixture becomes smooth.
Stir in water and vinegar and heat until bubbly.
Slice warm potatoes.
Add the sauce mixture with the crumbled bacon.
Stir gently and heat through.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain fat.
Cook green pepper, onion and celery until almost tender in a small amount of oil or butter. Combine meat, veggies and remaining ingredients.
Simmer all together until flavors are well blended.
The longer it cooks, the better it tastes.

title: green noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Cook hamburger lightly. Mix all together.
Top with butter and Ritz cracker crumbs.

title: chicken kabobs
directions: Marinate chicken 4 to 6 hours in oil, soy sauce, honey, lemon juice and garlic, stirring from time to time.
Alternate meat and vegetables and place onto skewers.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes over charcoal.
Keep turning.

title: peanut butter cookies the easy way
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: watergate salad
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: pear preserves
directions: Boil 1 1/2 cups sugar and water for 15 minutes.
Add pears. Boil 15 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar and lemon juice.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Put in jars.
Seal while hot.

title: sugar cream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 2 eggs and butter.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine 2 eggs, cream cheese and sugar.
Pour over cake batter.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: good plain cake
directions: Heat milk and butter to boiling.
Then add to rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pineapple buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar.
Heat to boil, stirring constantly. Remove and stir in jello.
Cool and then add frozen Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill in 8 x 12-inch pan.

title: cherry breeze
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk and blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Turn into crust.
Refrigerate 3 or 4 hours or until firm.
(Do not freeze.)
Top with cherry pie filling before stirring.

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: Mix together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs and milk.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Add other ingredients and bake in medium oven for 40 minutes.
Freezes well before it is cooked.

title: sugar nuts
directions: Melt butter (do not brown it) in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add dash of salt to egg whites and beat until soft mounds form.
Gradually add the sugar and beat until stiff mounds form.
Fold nuts into mixture.
Spread nut mixture over butter.
Stir well every 10 minutes for 30 minutes or until brown and all butter is absorbed. Put in oven at 350° and bake for 30 minutes.
Stir in large bowl.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes, adding milk to desired consistency; add ingredients and beat until smooth. Pour into buttered/sprayed 2-quart dish. Sprinkle paprika on top. Refrigerate overnight. Remove casserole from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: crunch top potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet in a 375° oven. Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces and place in a single layer. Turn once.
Mix rest of ingredients and sprinkle over potatoes. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Put everything in crock-pot on high for 30 minutes, then taste.
Add more seasonings to taste.
Cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: best ever pudding
directions: Use directions on package of pudding.
Thoroughly whip the cream to a froth.
Fold into pudding.
On a separate serving dish, alternate layers of wafers, thinly sliced bananas and pudding. Crush two or three wafers in hand and sprinkle over top.
Best served soon.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add other ingredients and cook until hot and bubbly.

title: no name hot dish
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed on pkg.
In a skillet, brown beef and green pepper together.
Combine all the ingredients with the beef, green pepper and macaroni; pour mixture into greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ranch style beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain; add catsup, mustard, water, onion soup, beans and brown sugar. Cook in crock-pot 5 or 6 hours. Cool and heat again.

title: dilled potato salad
directions: Cool potatoes.
Peel and cut in chunks.
Toss with remaining ingredients.
Chill before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hamburger steak deluxe
directions: Make 2 hamburger patties per person.
Cook 2 slices bacon per person until crisp.
Crumble bacon and place between 2 uncooked hamburger patties.
In same skillet of bacon drippings, cook the bacon filled steaks on each side until done.
Remove from skillet and drain grease, leaving approximately 1 tablespoonful.
Add the jar of mushrooms and 1 teaspoon beef bouillon.
Onion flakes can be added if you desire.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon flour; mix and stir constantly until thick.
Serve over steaks. Good with baked potatoes and green salad.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix
pudding and milk; add Cool Whip
and
sour
cream. Mix together.
Put layer of graham crackers, layer
of pudding mixture, layer of graham crackers, layer
of
pudding
mixture and layer of graham crackers.
Then top
with
chocolate
cake icing. Chill for 2 hours, then serve.

title: fresh okra muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Spoon into greased muffin pan. (Fill about 1/2 full.) Bake 20 minutes at 400°. Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: baked tomatoes with liver stuffing
directions: Cut thick slice from stem end of each tomato (save the top). Scoop out pulp.
Turn upside-down and drain.
Heat fat; add chopped liver and onion previously cooked and brown slightly.
Add bread crumbs, chopped mushrooms and seasoning.
Add enough of tomato pulp to moisten.
Fill tomatoes with mixture.
Cover with top slices and bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: lean beef and vegetable pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Trim fat from roast.
Spray a roasting pan with nonstick vegetable oil cooking spray.
Using medium heat, slowly brown the roast on all sides, turning it often.
Pour off any drippings.
Dissolve the bouillon cubes in 1 cup boiling water and add to meat along with the wine.
Add onions and garlic.
Cover and cook at 325° for 2 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Stir in soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until well blended.
Cover; chill 1 hour.
Stir before serving.

title: skillet chicken
directions: Coat cutlets with nonstick cooking spray and place in heated skillet.
Saute on each side for 2 minutes.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Add oil to skillet and saute garlic and mushrooms for 5 minutes.
Add crushed tomatoes and wine.
Cook for 10 minutes more.
Return chicken to skillet and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: lee graham's coffee punch
directions: Combine
coffee,
cocoa
and sugar.
Add boiling water, blending
until smooth.
Stir in cold water, vanilla and milk. Fold in
whipped
cream and ice cream just before serving.	(A regular punch bowl will hold 1/2 a recipe at a time.)

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix first four ingredients, reserve 1/3 of the topping. Alternate layers of wafers, bananas, and mixture. Top with remaining whipped topping. Keep refrigerated.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in milk, water coconut and melted butter.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: reunion scalloped potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes in a buttered baking dish (9 x 13-inch). Combine the remaining ingredients in a saucepan and stir over low heat until blended and cheese is melted.
Pour over potatoes. Bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pickles
directions: Fill a 1 gallon jar with clean whole (small) cucumbers.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Add water to fill container.
Let sit for 30 days.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Mix well.
Spread over a period of a lifetime.
Use often.

title: butter krispies
directions: Lay graham crackers in Jelly roll pan. Spread almonds over this. Boil butter, margarine and sugar for 2 minutes and pour over the crackers. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from pan when cool.

title: toledo mushroom casserole
directions: Put 1/2 the bread cubes in bottom of 7 1/2 x 12-inch oblong pan or casserole (buttered).
Combine onion, celery, green pepper, mayonnaise, salt and pepper; pour over bread.
Distribute mushrooms over top, then remaining bread.
Combine eggs with half and half; pour over all.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator overnight.
Before baking, spread mushroom soup over top.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese last 10 minutes.

title: johann-strauss salad
directions: Cover bottom of salad bowl with spinach.
Add chicken, crab, mushrooms and avocado.
Add French dressing or other and toss well.
Sprinkle with chopped egg.
Add garnish.

title: skillet stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into narrow strips. Mix salt, pepper and flour. Dredge steak strips in flour mixture. Place in skillet of hot oil. Brown on both sides. Add onions and saute until tender-crisp. Add beef broth and reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes. Add mushrooms; cover and simmer an additional 5 minutes. Add sour cream. Heat well; do not boil. Serve over hot rice or noodles.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, buttermilk, vanilla, and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: baked cranberries
directions: Place the cranberries in an 8 inch dish with cover. Add the sugar and water mixed together, cover, bake in a hot oven of 400 degrees for an hour. At 45 minutes, sprinkle with cinnamon. DO NOT STIR.

title: company stuffed pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Put in a baking pan.
Add rice, orange juice and soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 10 more minutes.
Serve.

title: summer berry pie
directions: Mix berries in large bowl.
Pour into pastry shell.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in medium saucepan.
Gradually stir in water until smooth, stirring constantly.

title: oatmeal chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine shortening, brown sugar, granulated sugar and salt.
Add eggs, nuts, vanilla, flour, oats and raisins.
Mix well.
Divide dough in half and roll each half in wax paper.
Chill overnight in freezer.
Then slice and bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: ham rolls
directions: Slice rolls in half. Mix all ingredients and spread on rolls. You can spread a little bit of extra butter on top of rolls before you bake them. Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: nicoise vinaigrette
directions: Whisk together until smooth.
Toss with cooked green beans and potatoes, fresh tomato slices, olives and croutons.
Makes 1 cup. Stores up to 1 month.

title: slender fries
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/2 inch wide sticks.
Wash and place in ice water 30 minutes. Drain, pat dry.
Put oil, paprika, salt in freezer bag.
Add potatoes and shake.
Place in pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 - 35 minutes.
Turn over once while baking.

title: yankee noodle dandies
directions: Melt pieces in top of double boiler over hot water.
Remove from heat and quickly add noodles and peanuts until they are evenly coated.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Chill. Store in refrigerator.
May be frozen.
Makes at least 36 pieces.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook vegetables. Drain and mix all together. Cover with bread crumbs. Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Let cool.
Peel and dice potatoes. In large pot, melt butter on medium heat.
Add flour and stir until well blended.
Increase heat to medium, slowly adding milk until mixture is almost to a boil.
Add potatoes, onions and bacon.
Stir in cheese and sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste. Heat until cheese is melted and serve.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Pour over chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: canned green beans
directions: To the beans add the cold water, sugar, vinegar, and salt.
Let mixture stand for 15 minutes then put on to boil.
Boil for 30 minutes and can in sterilized jars.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar.
Add oil and beat.
Sift dry ingredients.
Beat into creamed mixture.
Stir in pumpkin and vanilla.
Mix well.
Turn into 10-inch tube pan (greased and floured).
Bake in a 350° (preheated) oven for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil all ingredients except chicken
and
soup in water or chicken broth for 20 minutes.
Turn off
heat
and add soup and chicken.
Pour mixture into 15 x 9-inch
or
pie
pan that has been lined with pie crust (I use
Already
Pie
Crust in a refrigerator case) and cover with
second crust.
Crimp edges. Cook according to crust directions.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: wagon wheel sandwich
directions: Slice bread crosswise into 4 loaves.
On bottom layer put: 6 slices turkey breast, 6 slices American cheese and yellow mustard. On next bread, put: 6 slices roast beef, 6 slices Swiss cheese and horseradish.
On next bread, put: 6 slices ham, 8 strips fried bacon and salad dressing.
Add sliced tomato and lettuce.
Cut in pie wedges.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: shoe-peg corn casserole
directions: Mix together; put in 8 x 8-inch greased casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
The pepper flavor is better if you make and refrigerate overnight or several hours.

title: hot heros
directions: Mix and refrigerate for several hours.
Spread on French or Italian bread.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese and place in oven until cheese begins to melt.

title: creole cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar in mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla and buttermilk alternately with the flour, salt and cocoa that have been sifted together.
Last add boiling water mixed with soda.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 300° oven.
Batter will be thin.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding and pie filling, following package directions. Let stand until slightly thickened, 3 minutes.
Mix in condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Slice bananas into 1/2-inch rounds.

title: eggs in a pocket
directions: Combine eggs, Velveeta cheese, Miracle Whip, celery and olives; mix lightly.
Cover and chill.
Fill pita halves with lettuce, tomatoes and egg mixture.

title: shrimp dilly dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except shrimp.
Add the shrimp. Chill.
Serve on crackers.

title: german nutmeg coffee cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients until crumbly.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Beat egg until foamy.
Add buttermilk and soda.
Combine this with dry ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup reserved ingredients on top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: nacho salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and pour Catalina dressing over top.
Chill and serve.

title: pickled beets
directions: Wash and cook, beets until tender.
Peel and slice in bottle. Mix ingredients above and bring to boiling point.
Do not boil. Pour over beets and sprinkle a little pepper on top of each bottle to taste.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Pour into baked pie crust.
Add Dream Whip.
Makes 2 large pies.

title: spicy beef dip
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic. Stir in tomato sauce, oregano and sugar. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Add cream cheese and Parmesan until cheese melts. Dip with Doritos.

title: grandma's chunk sweet pickles
directions: Clean cucumbers.
Put in a large bowl.
Pour boiling water on whole cucumbers for 4 mornings.
Fifth morning, cut pickles into 1/2 to 3/4-inch chunks, discarding ends.
Make syrup with sugar, vinegar, salt and spices.
Pour hot syrup over cucumbers.
Reheat syrup on mornings 6 and 7.
On morning 8, simmer syrup for 5 minutes; add food coloring and can.

title: vegetable dip
directions: In small bowl, blend soup mix with mayonnaise, sour cream and lemon juice.
Add spinach.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Combine and place in buttered baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger zucchini casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and salt in oil; drain.
In 1 1/2-quart greased casserole, layer as follows:
zucchini, half of meat mixture, mushrooms, Mozzarella cheese and remaining meat mixture. Pour tomato sauce over.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 60 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: pastel pound cake
directions: Beat all ingredients except nuts for 3 minutes or until smooth.
Dredge nuts in flour and fold into mixture.
Pour batter into well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In a saucepan, heat the peach slices and butter.
Pour into glass baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk; beat until lumps are out.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° until crust comes to top and is brown.

title: hi-fiber granola
directions: *Other spices, such as nutmeg, cloves or allspice, may be used for variety.

title: whizzer rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Pour scalded milk over shortening, salt and sugar.
Cool.
Add yeast and beaten eggs.
Add flour; beat vigorously.
Cover and let raise 1 hour.
Stir up and spoon into greased muffin tins.
Let raise 1/2 hour.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
