directions: Saute broccoli, onion and carrots in butter until vegetables are tender.
Stir in milk and soup and cook until tender.

title: onion squares
directions: Cook onions in butter until translucent.
Cool.
Blend sour cream, flour, salt and caraway seed.
Beat eggs and add to sour cream.
Blend in bacon and onions.
Pat crescent rolls in 9-inch square pan.
Pour in onion mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes. Cool slightly and cut into 16 squares.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Swirls of apple-filled pastry make this cobbler an all-time Martha White favorite.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough in pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes (enough for 8 x
13-inch	or
8 x 12-inch dish) in skins until half done,
then
grate into baking dish. Melt butter.
Add cheese, onions,
salt	and pepper.
Add sour cream; mix.
Dot with 2
tablespoons butter.
Pour over grated potatoes. Mix.
Put in dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and stuffing surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can be topped with warm cream of mushroom or cream of chicken soup when served.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer in order the crumbs, coconut, chips, milk and nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Cool and cut 1 x 3-inch bars.
Makes 36.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend oil, sugar, pumpkin and eggs well.
Mix in baking powder, baking soda, nutmeg, cloves and cinnamon.
Sift in flour; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Mix well. Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: beef and rigatoni stew
directions: Stew prunes for 5 minutes and pit.
Shake beef cubes in a bag with flour and 1 teaspoon salt, a few at a time, until all are coated.
Brown beef in hot oil in deep 4-quart Dutch oven.
Add onion, garlic, salt, pepper, oregano and Tabasco.
Add tomato sauce and enough hot water to keep liquid 1 inch above meat.
Stir well, cover tightly and bake in slow oven (300°) for 2 hours. Add rigatoni, prunes and more water.
Cover; bake 1 hour longer. Serve with green salad, rolls and light dessert.
Enjoy.

title: hobo
directions: Cook bacon, remove and add onions to bacon grease.
Cook until clear.
Add meat and cook until it has lost its red color.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until liquid is reduced.
Serve over cornbread squares.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Fry bacon in soup pot until crisp; drain, reserving 2 tablespoons pan drippings.
Saute celery, onion and carrots in reserved pan drippings over medium heat until tender.
Add potatoes.
Cook until slightly browned, stirring frequently.
Add milk.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat for 30 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Mix sour cream and flour in small bowl.
Stir into soup.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes or to desired consistency.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.

title: mrs. aiken's cream pie(1940)
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Add scalded milk. Cook in double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour small amount of mixture over eggs, stirring vigorously.
Return to double boiler and cook 10 minutes longer.
Add vanilla and cool, then pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip or use meringue.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together 2 1/2 cups flour, cinnamon, soda, allspice and salt.
Add pumpkin and sugar mixture, blending well.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending after each addition.
Combine nuts, remaining flour and raisins.
Add to pumpkin mixture.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: On an ungreased cookie sheet, unroll crescent rolls so that they form a "crust." Cook as directed and let cool. Chop tomato, broccoli, cauliflower and green onions; drain olives. Spread cream cheese over "crust" and layer cheese, olives and vegetables. Let chill. Cut into squares and serve.

title: saturday night special
directions: Precook bacon.
Set aside.
Brown meat, stirring frequently. Drain.
Add pork and beans, onion, salt and brown sugar.
Put in casserole dish; top with strips of bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salad
directions: Chop pears and pineapple.
Mix together and serve plain or on lettuce.

title: corned beef dip
directions: In food processor chop onion and beef or corned beef. Add to sour cream, mayonnaise, parsley, dill weed and Beau Monde.
Chill several hours or even better overnight.
Hollow out first loaf and cut the rest into large cubes.

title: apricot sherbet
directions: Place apricots in container of an electric blender; process until smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides.
Combine apricot puree, sugar and remaining ingredients.
Pour into freezer container of a 1-gallon hand-turned or electric freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions and serve.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: snowy white potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes about 15 minutes or until tender.
Mash potatoes in large bowl with electric mixer.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic.
Beat at high speed until smooth and light.
Stir in chives.
Spoon into lightly greased baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika and dot with butter.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes until lightly golden and heated through.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix together butter, sugar, eggs, sour cream and vanilla. Sift together flour, baking powder and soda.
Pour 1/2 mixture into greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle topping on.

title: salt water taffy
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Add butter and cook without stirring to 290°.
Add vanilla extract and cream of tartar.
Pour into a buttered pan.
When cool enough to handle, pull until white.
Cut and wrap in waxed paper.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onions, salt and garlic salt in a large bowl.
Fold in potatoes.
Spoon into casserole.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: chicken crescent wreath
directions: Arrange crescent rolls on 12 inch pizza pan, forming a ring with pointed ends facing outer edge of pan and wide ends overlapping.
Combine the remaining ingredients and spoon over wide ends of rolls.
Fold points over filling and tuck under wide ends, (filling will be visible).
Bake at 375 degrees for 20 to 25minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 - 8 servings.

title: pennsylvania dutch chow chow(makes 8 to 10 quarts)
directions: Chop all vegetables to desired size and cook each separately or use canned vegetables where you can.
Drain vegetables and mix together.
Combine vinegar, sugar and water.
Bring to boil.
Add turmeric and salt.
Add all the vegetables to hot liquid and bring to a boil.
Pack in hot jars.

title: nabisco dessert
directions: Grind cookies fine.
Pack 2/3 in 9 x 13-inch pan; pat firmly. Cream butter, sugar and eggs; put on top of ground cookies.
Chop nuts; spread on top of cream layer.
Add apricots (chopped fine), then spread Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle with remaining ground cookies.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 12 hours.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, melt butter. Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down gently. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and pineapple juice.
Whip until creamy in mixer.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Chill.

title: oven stew
directions: Put all ingredients in covered casserole dish in 325° oven for 3 to 4 hours.
Fifteen minutes before serving, add one can of mixed vegetables and small whole carrots.

title: lime luncheon salad
directions: Dissolve jello in cup of hot water, add pineapple juice and cool.
Add cabbage, pineapple, nuts and marshmallows.
Let stand until it is almost jelled, then fold in whipped cream and mayonnaise.
Pour in Pyrex pan and refrigerate.

title: caramel pecan pinwheels
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9-inch round baking pan.
Combine ice cream topping and butter in the baking pan; sprinkle nuts over.
Separate the bread sticks, but do not uncoil them.
Arrange in pan with sides touching.
Bake until golden, about 25 minutes. Let stand in pan 5 to 10 minutes, then invert on serving plate. Yields 10 rolls.

title: pistachio jello salad
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: oven french fries
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut in long strips 1/2-inch wide.
Dry strips with paper towels.
Toss in a bowl with oil.
When strips are well coated with oil, spread them in a single layer on cookie sheet. Place in a 450° oven for 35 minutes.
Turn on sides to brown on all sides.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Saute peppers, onions and celery in butter.
Add shrimp mixture.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and completely cover with lemon slices.
Cook, covered, for about 20 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6. May be frozen ahead.

title: nuts-for-chocolate bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour and 1/2 cup sugar in small bowl. Cut in 1/2 cup margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Press firmly into bottom of a greased, foil-lined 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes until edges are lightly browned. Microwave chocolate and 1/4 cup margarine on High for 1 1/2 minutes until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Stir in corn syrup, 1/2 cup sugar, eggs and vanilla. Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: zucchini and egg on rolls
directions: Slice zucchini (skin on) very thin.
Saute in butter and olive oil until crispy and golden.
Sprinkle with paprika and garlic. In another frying pan, scramble eggs.
Add zucchini mixture, serve on warm, buttered rolls.

title: low-fat vegetarian burritos
directions: Slice peppers in strips lengthwise; discard the stem but use the seeds.
Slice onion and separate in rings.
Chop garlic. Spray a nonstick skillet with cooking spray and stir-fry until tender.
Season lightly with lite salt and creole seasoning. Drain beans and mash with a potato masher until spreadable. Warm tortillas in foil.

title: watergate salad or dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients, any order.
Let set in bowl in refrigerator overnight.

title: 10-egg pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco. Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and milk, then flavoring; mix well. Put in a large greased tube pan. Bake for 2 hours at 300° or until done. Will make 1 Bundt cake and 1 small loaf cake. Cut down on the time; bake for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: yeast bread
directions: Combine yeast and 1/2 cup warm tap water.
Add 2 cups water, sugar, milk and oil.
Mix and add a little flour until it gets not to hard but soft.

title: meat loaf for 24
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 3 loaves and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 24.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in salt water (1/3 cup canning salt and water to cover cucumbers).
Soak for 4 hours, then drain well.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Debone cooked chicken, place in a greased casserole.
Heat cream of chicken soup and cream cheese over low heat.
Pour over chicken.
Melt butter.
Crush crackers and add poppy seed.
Mix with butter and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: artichoke cheese dip
directions: Chop and drain artichokes and chilies.
Stir in mayonnaise and cheeses, also seasonings.
Put in a casserole and bake for 1 hour in a 375° oven.
Serve with crackers or sliced and toasted pita bread.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate cream cake
directions: In small bowl chill 2 cups frosting mix, the whipping cream and 2 teaspoons instant coffee; mix and chill at least 1 hour.
Bake cake in two round layer pans.
Add 1 tablespoon coffee to mix. Split cake after cool to make 4 layers.
Beat frosting mixture until stiff, fill between layers.
Spread top of cake with thin icing allowing some to drizzle down sides.
Chill before serving.

title: corn cob jelly
directions: Wash cobs and cut into 4-inch lengths.
Place in container. Add 2-quarts water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and boil slowly for 35 to 40 minutes.
Strain juice, measure out 3 cups juice into large container.
Add sugar and again bring to a boiling point.
Boil 5 minutes.
Skim.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Add yeast to water.
Melt shortening; scald milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
In a bowl, put milk, oil, salt, sugar and 2 cups flour. Beat and add yeast and egg.
Mix; add remaining flour.
Knead on floured board 20 times; divide into rolls in greased pan.
Rise about 1 hour.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Dough can be refrigerated for several days.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with crackers.
If too stiff, add a little milk or cream.

title: wild plum tea muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Pour into a well-greased miniature muffin tin, filling half full. Bake in 325° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: company chicken
directions: Pepper the boned, halved chicken breasts.
Place chicken in long baking dish on top of chipped beef.
Cover with soup, sour cream and cream cheese.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine
all and form balls.
Roll in powdered sugar, chopped nuts and coconut.
Makes 70.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix boiling water with jello for 2 minutes until fully dissolved.
Add undrained pineapple and blueberry pie filling. Mix well, pour into a casserole dish and chill until firm.

title: u.s.s.  missouri buttermilk pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, gradually beat the sugar into the softened butter with an electric mixer, beating until mixture is well blended.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine the all-purpose flour and the salt. Gradually beat these dry ingredients into the butter mixture. Beat in the buttermilk until mixture is well blended.
Pour the egg and buttermilk filling into the pie crust.
Sprinkle the toasted pecans over the top of the filling in the pie crust.

title: basic play dough(not for human consumption)
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil.
Stir in oil, alum and food coloring.
Add 2 cups flour and quickly knead.

title: punch
directions: Mix jello,
sugar,
water and pineapple juice.	Freeze. Thaw 3 to 4 hours before serving.	Add 7-Up.

title: sweet and sour brussels sprouts
directions: Dice onion.
Fry with bacon.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Pour mixture over cooked Brussels sprouts.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Grease square pan.
Mix eggs, oil, salt, pepper and parsley. In separate bowl, mix zucchini, onion, Bisquick and cheese.
Add to mixture and fold in.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Mix alternately with buttermilk, soda, almond extract, vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt. Grease and flour Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then lower to 325° for 25 minutes. Cool and remove from pan.

title: quick almond fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts, in top of double boiler. Place over simmering water and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and mix.
Spread candy quickly in buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cool. Cut in squares.
Yields about 2 dozen pieces.

title: ruby sauced beets
directions: Blend cornstarch, sugar and salt in a large saucepan. Stir in cranberry juice cocktail. Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly. Add drained beets and orange peel.
Heat and serve. Serves 10 to 12.

title: zucchini boats with ham and vegetable stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut zucchini lengthwise in half.
Scoop out inside and leave 1/2-inch thick shell. Save inside and cut into pieces (small).
Place zucchini, cut side down, in pan large enough to hold it, and fill pan with one-inch deep of hot water. Put in oven and cook until shell softens some (between 5 and 10 minutes).
While zucchini is softening shell, do the following:

title: no knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs and half of flour and yeast mixture.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Blend in remaining flour.
Place in oiled bowl.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Form into rolls.
Score each roll; brush with melted butter or margarine.
Fold over and place in oiled pan and brush tops.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: deluxe chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all but instant potatoes together in a saucepan, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Season to taste.

title: blueberry - cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Press dough evenly in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Beat cream cheese, egg, sugar and lemon rind with mixer until smooth.
Spread cheese mixture over cookie dough.
Dollop blueberry pie filling on cheese and swirl with knife.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool, cut and refrigerate.

title: schur's secret rib recipe
directions: Cook over a slow fire.
Must cook at least 3 hours to tenderize.
I favor a charcoal smoker with a water pan.
Use hardwood briquets, as they burn slower.
Use soaked hickory chips and add hourly.
Season ribs with lemon pepper.
Baste every 30 to 45 minutes with barbecue sauce.
Last 30 minutes baste with honey mixture which has been cut with lemon juice.
Serve ribs while still hot.

title: beer bread
directions: Pour all ingredients except butter into loaf pan and mix well. Pour butter over top and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: any fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in 2 1/2-quart glass dish in oven.
Add fruit and mix with butter.

title: homemade bailey's
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly with a whisk or whip.
Pour into a sterilized bottle; cover and chill.
Serve as you like. Expiration date is the same as the eggs used.
Makes approximately 1/5 of Bailey's.

title: joyce higdon's blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in one cup of boiling water.
Add pineapple and blueberries.
Chill until set.
Sprinkle pecans on top.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Cook egg, salt, sugar and vinegar until thick.
Add margarine. Serve over shredded cabbage.

title: au gratin chicken bake
directions: Combine
chicken, soup, water chestnuts, spaghetti, 1/2 cup Cheddar
cheese,
1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, milk, pimiento and
soy sauce;
mix
lightly.
Spoon into 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and
additional Parmesan cheese; continue baking until cheese melts.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: shepherd's pie casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
In casserole dish, layer hamburger and onion soup mix, then frozen Tater Tots.
Mix soups and milk. Pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese. Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil water, sugar and cloves for 10 minutes.
Add the lemon and orange juice.
Add to tea.

title: deviled ham and cheese log
directions: Blend ham, cheese, pecans and seasoning.
Shape into a roll. Sprinkle paprika generously on wax paper.
Roll log to coat evenly with paprika.
Wrap in wax paper; chill overnight.
Slice to serve or spread on crackers.
(This even makes a good sandwich.)

title: nut brittle
directions: Butter large cookie sheet or spray with Pam.
Combine nuts, sugar and corn syrup in medium size heavy pan.
Bring to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly, 10 to 15 minutes.
Boil without stirring until it reaches 295° on a candy thermometer, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda (mixture will foam up).
Stir quickly until blended and quickly pour onto cookie sheet.
Spread with thin spatula as thin as possible.
Cool completely.
Break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: taylor's pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy; stir in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Mix well.
Blend in dry ingredients, except nuts and raisins.
Add nuts and raisins; stir well.

title: sweet-sour pork
directions: Brown pork slightly in hot fat.
Add water; cover and cook slowly 1 hour.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt, vinegar, pineapple juice and soy sauce.
Mix. Cook until slightly thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over hot, cooked pork.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add green pepper, onion and pineapple chunks and cook only 2 or 3 minutes.
Serve with hot fluffy rice.
(Chinese noodles are good with it, too.)

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Melt butter.
Slowly add flour to butter.
Add broth and water.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring as much as possible. Simmer on low heat for 15 minutes.

title: paella
directions: Brown rice in olive oil until brown.
Remove from pan.
Saute onions, garlic, sausage, peppers in olive oil and whatever other vegetables and raw meat you use.
Add rice, chicken broth and paprika (adjust quantity) and bring to boil.
Add saffron, pinch only, boil 8 minutes.
Add shellfish.
Bury shellfish in rice. Simmer until rice absorbs all liquid.
Do not cover.

title: chicken pecan salad
directions: Toast pecans in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix pecans, chicken, celery, onions and bacon in large bowl.
Add mayonnaise, sour cream, salt and lemon juice, tossing well.
Spoon salad on bed of lettuce.
Garnish with tomato wedges, cold asparagus spears or hard-boiled eggs.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: aunt helen's spoon bread
directions: Stir the meal into 3 cups of milk.
Let this come to a boil, making a mush.
Cool.
Add well beaten eggs, salt, baking powder and melted butter.
Bake in a medium oven 30 minutes.
Serve in the dish in which the bread was baked.
A casserole is the preferable type to use.

title: tangy poppy seed fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve 1/4 cup of juice.
Combine pineapple with orange, kiwi, grapes and strawberries in large bowl.
Stir reserved juice with lime peel, lime juice, honey and poppy seeds and pour over fruit.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Layer in following order in 9 x 13-inch pan:
refried beans, mashed avocados (put lemon in with avocados), chopped tomatoes, onion and olives.
Mix together sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning; spread over top for fourth layer.
Add grated cheese. Dip with chips and enjoy.

title: drop-a-kiss cookies
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Form into 1 inch balls and place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Take out of oven and immediately plant a kiss in the center of the cookie.
Let cool and eat.

title: rico's buffalo wings
directions: Fry wings in oil; do not batter. Combine hot sauce, margarine and seasonings in saucepan on very low heat. Add vinegar.
Pour sauce over wings in a bowl with a lid. Shake and enjoy.

title: polish sauerkraut
directions: Saute mushrooms, onions, and pepper in butter. In crock-pot or Dutch oven, cook smoked sausage until heated thoroughly. Add sauteed vegetables, kraut, tomatoes, salt, and pepper. Cook in crock-pot on high 3 to 4 hours. In Dutch oven, cook about 1 1/2 hours.

title: honey-moist cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, stir together flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: homemade playdough
directions: Mix together and cook over medium heat until it forms a ball (it will be thick); cool, knead and its ready to play.
Caution: it's definitely not for eating.

title: ham salad(skinkesalat)
directions: Arrange lettuce leaves in a large salad bowl.
Mix ham, vegetables and fruit and pile on lettuce.
Mix yogurt and mustard and spoon over vegetables.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: scallops bonne femme
directions: In large skillet over medium heat and in hot butter, cook onion until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add scallops, mushrooms, wine and lemon juice.
Reduce heat to medium low; cover and cook until scallops are just tender, about 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: sauerkraut-tomato dish
directions: Fry bacon just until crisp.
Add diced onion; saute until tender, but not brown.
Mix the tomatoes and sauerkraut.
Add sugar; mix again.
Add the bacon and onion mixture.
Bake for 2 hours or so at 325°.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and seasoning. Stir in onions, spinach, water chestnuts and red peppers.
Cover and refrigerate to blend flavors.
Serve with crisp vegetable dippers, assorted crackers or bread.

title: stuffed mushrooms(microwave)
directions: Wash mushrooms, remove stem from each cap by twisting.
Arrange caps, stem-side-up, in 3-quart (13 x 9-inch) glass baking dish; set aside.
Chop stems fine.
Place stems, onions and butter in medium glass mixing bowl.
Microwave for 3 minutes on Roast or until onions are tender.
Stir in sour cream; add cream cheese. Microwave for 2 1/2 minutes, on Roast, or until cream cheese is softened; stir well.
Divide mixture into four (6-ounce) custard cups.
Stir ingredients from one of the variations into each cup. Fill mushrooms caps with one of the cream mixtures.
Microwave for 5 to 6 minutes on Roast, or until hot.
Makes about 36 mushrooms. Roast = 70% power.

title: old fashion dutch apple cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, 3/4 c. sugar, and brown sugar

together. Cut in the shortening with pastry blender. Beat egg with milk and vanilla in separate bowl. Stir into dry ingredients. Pour into lightly greased square pan. Cover dough with apple slices arranged in rows. Sprinkle with 1/2 c. sugar, cinnamon, coconut and drizzle with melted butter. Bake 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: walnut bread
directions: Mix with milk and bake in a warm oven in loaf pans.
Keep the dough fairly moist but easy to handle.

title: bettye's peach cream cake
directions: Line bottom of Pyrex dish with angel food cake, broken in bite size pieces.
Prepare vanilla pudding according to instructions on box.
(I use a little less milk to make the pudding a little thicker.)
Put in refrigerator until cold.

title: carrot cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except walnuts. Blend on low speed of mixer until moistened.
Beat on high speed 1 minute.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: janette's black-eyed pea dip
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place peas in heavy medium saucepan and add enough water to cover by 2 inches.
Let stand with garlic for 1/2 hour, then boil until peas are tender, about 1 hour, adding water, if necessary.
Drain and place in food processor with remaining ingredients except for the cheese and onions.
Pulse until smooth, and season with salt and pepper.
Place in 8-inch pie plate and warm in oven at 400° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese, wait until melted, and then garnish with the green onions. Serve with white corn chips.

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown sausage. Add onion and cut cheese into blocks.
Add tomatoes (drained). Cook on stove until all ingredients are blended well. Either serve cool or transfer to crock-pot. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: grandma bentley's sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, nutmeg and salt together.
Cream shortening and gradually add sugar.
Cream until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add lemon extract. Combine vinegar and milk and add to creamed mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
Roll about 1/8-inch thick on floured board. Cut and place on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 370° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Layer noodles and chicken mixture into 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes until bubbly.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 (8-inch) unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, baking soda, water, oil, 1 teaspoon salt, vinegar, flour and cocoa; blend well.
Fill tins 1/3 of way.
In small bowl, mix the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, egg and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Gradually mix in chocolate chips.
Put 1 heaping teaspoonful of filling on top of other mix.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Best if small tins are used.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: chicken maryland(4 servings)
directions: In skillet, saute chicken in 3 teaspoons butter until brown and tender, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove to hot platter.
Stir flour into pan drippings.
Add milk.
Stir until thickened.
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoon butter in saucepan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in sherry.
Add white sauce to mushroom mixture. Serve sauce over chicken.

title: chocolate sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. For cake, cream butter and sugar in a large bowl until fluffy. Add eggs, beating until smooth. In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, and salt. Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, blending well. Gently fold in sour cream and vanilla. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons topping in bottom of greased and floured 9-inch tube pan. Spoon half of cake batter into pan. Sprinkle 4 tablespoons topping over batter and drizzle half of glaze over topping. Spoon remaining batter into pan and sprinkle with remaining topping. Reserve remaining glaze. Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until a toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean. Cool in pan. Transfer to a serving plate. Reheat remaining glaze and drizzle over cake.

title: dinner casserole
directions: Rinse frozen peas and carrots under running water until separated; drain.
Mix peas and carrots with remaining ingredients (except chips) in ungreased casserole or baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Sprinkle with chips.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven until hot and bubbly, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lazy day salad
directions: In large bowl mix pudding and pineapple.
Stir in oranges and fruit cocktail. Fold in whipped topping.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together and pour in baking dish.
Cook for 1 hour at 400°.
Crumble together butter and cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over top and bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix and place in a 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Do not overbake because they are a soft cookie.

title: zucchini puffs
directions: Mix ingredients and fry in cakes to a golden brown.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Brown
hamburger
in skillet;
drain well.
Add chopped onion and seasonings to taste.
Stir in soup and about 1/2 can of water.
Simmer
for
10 minutes.
Just before serving, add sour cream; heat through, but not to boiling.
Great over rice or noodles.

title: picnic salad
directions: Mix ingredients and serve.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown hamburger, stirring to separate meat; drain.
Add onion, canned tomatoes, Tabasco sauce and salt.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add kidney beans and reheat before serving.
Yield:
4 servings.
Carbohydrate 17 g, protein 22 g, fat 9 g, calories 237.
One serving = 3 meat low-fat exchange, 1 bread starch exchange.

title: potato latkes
directions: You will need a large frying pan with a lot of oil.

title: yum yum jello salad
directions: Drain juice off pineapple and
add
water to make 1 cup liquid.
Boil juice;
remove
from	heat.
Add
jello and dissolve.
Add ice cream
and
stir
well.	Add other ingredients and pinch of salt.	Let set
for
at
least 2 hours to congeal before serving.
Will keep for some time in refrigerator.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add thawed and drained strawberries and pineapple.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in mold.
Let stand in refrigerator until partly set.
Put sour cream on top of mixture, then rest of jello mixture.
Refrigerate until fully set.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Place in a bowl in layers in order ingredients are listed. Sprinkle bacon on top.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.
Toss salad before serving.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients.
Pour
into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until filling is set.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour and stir into blackberries.
Pour into pie shells.

title: chance's favorite cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in iron skillet and pour in cornmeal.
Sprinkle skillet with cornmeal.
Mix cornmeal mix with egg, butter and water until desired consistency.
Bake until brown.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Stir in butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients and let stand overnight.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: holiday ribbon ring
directions: Dissolve strawberry flavored gelatin in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Pour 1 1/2 cups in 6-cup mold.
Chill until set but not firm.
Chill remaining gelatin in bowl.
Gradually blend in 1/3 cup sour cream and spoon over gelatin in mold.
Chill set. Repeat with lime flavored gelatin.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt oleo in small roaster, add Minute rice.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with 3 1/2 cups water.
Sprinkle 1 package onion soup mix over all.
Add cut up chicken pieces or boneless chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: german beets
directions: Simmer onions in melted butter until tender.
Stir in sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add water and vinegar.
Add beets and simmer for 30 minutes to blend flavors.

title: canned pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs, pumpkin and water. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased wide mouth pint jars filling them half full of batter.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.
When done, remove one jar at a time from oven, clean sealing edge and screw on lids firmly tight.
The bread may be frozen by allowing it to cool in the jars and then put on lids. Screwing them on tightly and store in freezer.
Makes 8 pints.

title: roll-out cookie recipe(faith's sugar cookie recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar with electric mixer.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add baking powder and flour, one cup at a time, mixing after each addition. The dough will be very stiff; blend last flour in by hand.
Do not chill dough.
Divide dough into 2 balls.
On a floured surface, roll each ball in a circle, approximately 12-inches in diameter and 1/8-inch thick.
Dip cutters in flour before each use. Sprinkle on any candy trims before baking.
Bake cookies on ungreased cookie sheet on middle rack of oven for 4 to 5 minutes, depending on size or until cookies are lightly browned.
Using a spatula, remove cookies from cookie sheet and allow to cool on a wire rack.

title: original coney island hot dog sauce
directions: Simmer everything, except hot dogs, until thick.
Grind hot dogs, add and cook 15 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and milk.
Add vanilla, coconut and oleo. Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: skillet sausage and potato and pepper
directions: Brown potatoes.
When almost done; add peppers and sausage. When heated through, add tomatoes.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: holiday stuffing
directions: In a large skillet, heat butter; saute vegetables and shallots until tender, about 10 minutes.
In a large bowl, combine sauteed vegetables, bread cubes, grapes, seasonings and enough pan drippings or broth to moisten (do not saturate).

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage with onion.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Combine ingredients in a baking dish.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for approximately 25 to 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: buttermilk bran muffins
directions: Combine shredded wheat, raisin bran, All-Bran and hot water. Let stand; set aside.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream together salad oil and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat in mixture.
Add flour and buttermilk.
May store in covered container in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Fill muffin pans 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 1 large or 2 small balls. Roll in crushed pecans.
Grape-Nuts cereal works well if you don't have pecans.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients; form a ball.
Roll in 2 packages Buddig thin sliced, chopped beef.

title: sausage-apple loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9x5x3 inch pan and line bottom with greased waxed paper.
In large bowl beat eggs with seasonings and mustard.
Stir in bread crumbs, applesauce and onion.
Add half the sausage and work with your hands or a fork, until evenly mixed.
Work in remaining meat and firmly press into pan. Lay a sheet of foil over top and bake in center of oven for 1 hour.
Remove foil and drain fat.
Continue baking, uncovered for 45 minutes more.

title: sugar spiced pecans
directions: In one-quart microwavable shallow casserole, combine butter, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves; microwave on High (100%) for 1 minute, until melted.
Add pecans and stir to coat; microwave on High for 2 minutes, until pecans are glazed.
Transfer nuts to sheet of wax paper, set aside and let cool, until sugar mixture hardens, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: 1,2,3 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten egg yolks. Mix well. Sift flour and baking powder. Add to butter mixture. Add milk and vanilla. Fold in stiff beaten egg whites. Pour into 3 greased and floured pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes or until done.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli, drain.
Arrange on greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Pour over the chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter, sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: kidney bean casserole
directions: Place 4 slices bacon in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or a 3-quart casserole.
Cover with 2 cans of beans.
Layer on top, in order:
onions, peppers and tomatoes.
Cover with rest of the beans.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Place 4 slices of bacon over the mixture.
Pour ketchup over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, uncovered.
Cover; bake an additional 1 hour.

title: chocolate "philly" fudge
directions: Place softened cream cheese in bowl; beat slightly.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits 5 minutes and mix in other ingredients.
Put into 9 x 13-inch glass, greased baking dish and bake 1 hour at 250°.
Can freeze in small portions.
Very good.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove the bones.
Cut up in small pieces (bite size).
Make sure to add enough water to the chicken so you will have at least a quart of broth left, as you will need some for the dressing and some for gravy in case you want to use it.

title: apple cranberry punch
directions: Crush cranberry sauce in can with fork; put in saucepan and gradually beat in water with egg beater.
Add cider, cinnamon and cloves.
Simmer 5 minutes; add orange juice and serve hot.
Keeps well and may be reheated.

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: Combine milk, pie filling mix, pumpkin, spices and whipped topping in a deep, narrow-bottomed bowl.
Beat at lowest speed of electric mixer for 1 minute.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until set, at least 3 hours.
Garnish with additional topping and pecans, if desired.

title: mexican dip
directions: I use a square Pyrex dish, medium size. Mash the black beans into the bottom of the dish. Spread the cream cheese over the black beans. Spread the salsa over cream cheese. Spread the shredded cheese over the salsa. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes (your judgment). Enjoy with your favorite dipping chip.

title: chinese chews
directions: Melt morsels over warm water slowly until all melted.
Then take the pan out and add the noodles and peanuts and stir well. Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.
Let them set.
You can freeze them or keep in refrigerator.
Takes 15 minutes to make.
You may add a few more nuts, if you wish.
Good also with cashew nuts.

title: sherried chicken
directions: Lightly brown chicken breasts in butter.
Then remove to a 8 x 10-inch casserole dish.
Brown 2 onions, add mushrooms, drained. Add a little flour, about 2 tablespoons and liquid from mushrooms, also, 1/2 cup sherry.
Pour over chicken and cook in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Mix together 1/2 pint sour cream and 1/2 cup sherry. Pour this over chicken and replace in oven for 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Excellent pie served with ice cream and warm sauce topping.

title: hearty ham casserole
directions: Mix cooked macaroni and all ingredients except chips.
Pour mixture into buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: home freezer ice cream
directions: Scald whole milk.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add to scalded milk.
Cook mixture over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens like custard.
Remove from heat and cool. Add cream or cream mixture (not beaten) and vanilla.
Cool thoroughly and freeze according to freezer instructions.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt margarine in bottom of pan. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly.
Sprinkle coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and pecans.
Press firmly. Pour milk over whole mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crazy bread
directions: Mix well.
Add thawed and drained broccoli last.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Cream together margarine, brown sugar, powdered sugar and spices. Boil water. Place mix, approximately 2 tablespoons, into mug. Add boiling water and rum to taste. Mix may be refrigerated for later use.

title: mexican hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and deep fry until golden brown.

title: lynne's cincinnati chili
directions: In 4-quart oven, combine water, tomato sauce, onions, chili powder, vinegar, Worcestershire, cinnamon, salt, cumin, allspice, cloves, garlic powder, chocolate, bay leaf and chili pepper.
Bring to boil.
Crumble meat and add slowly to boiling liquid.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 hours, uncovered, until thickened as desired.
Remove bay leaf and chili pepper.
Top with chopped onion, shredded cheese and/or kidney beans.
Makes 5 cups.

title: tea cakes(makes 50 old fashioned cakes)
directions: Melt butter or oleo and let cool.
Beat eggs well.
Mix all ingredients except flour, which is added gradually to egg mixture. When dough becomes stiff enough to handle, knead on floured board or cloth.
Roll out and cut.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from greased cookie sheet immediately and cool. Store in tins.

title: lazy cabbage rolls casserole
directions: Use a 2 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Brown beef, add salt, pepper and onions, drain off grease.
Add rice, soup and water.
Cook and mix well 2-3 minutes.

title: corn and pea salad
directions: Place all drained and chopped vegetables in a bowl.
Boil oil, sugar and vinegar for 5 minutes.
Cool and pour over vegetables.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Mix together the first four ingredients in a large saucepan. Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from the heat and add the oats, peanut butter and vanilla flavoring.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper and let set.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Combine oats, brown sugar and buttermilk in a bowl. Let stand for 10 minutes.
Add egg and oil; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and stir just enough to moisten.
Spoon batter into greased or paper-lined muffin cups, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: venison rotini soup
directions: Brown meat.
Add the rest of ingredients and bring to a boil. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Garnish with sour cream and chives.

title: pork barbecue sauce(mildred gregory)
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Add 1 cup catsup, pork (already roasted and chopped).
Also add a tablespoon or 2 of Worcestershire sauce.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Grind 1 1/2 pounds of the chocolate finely in a food processor.
In a small saucepan, bring the whipping cream just to the boil.
With the processor running, pour the warm whipping cream into the chocolate through the feed tube.
Continue mixing until the chocolate is smooth, stopping as necessary to scrape down the sides of the work bowl.
Refrigerate the mixture in the covered processor bowl until cool, about 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend together and make a well in center & add the filling.

title: bar-b-que chicken
directions: Saute diced onion in skillet sprayed with non-stick cooking spray.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Place in skillet with onion.
Stir together Diet Coke, ketchup and mustard.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove lid and simmer until liquid is cooked down.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Clean broccoli and cauliflower and allow to air-dry.

title: pot roast
directions: Season the roast well the day before it is to be cooked with plenty of salt and pepper or the lemon pepper marinade.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix for 2 minutes, then add 1/2 cup nuts and mix/stir.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Slowly add sugar and salt.
Add vanilla and fold in chocolate bits and nuts.
Lay a sheet of aluminum foil on bottom of cookie sheet.
Drop cookies by teaspoonfuls on foil.
Place in oven.
Turn off heat immediately.
Leave in oven overnight.
Do not open until morning.

title: cream of anything casserole
directions: Line bottom of casserole dish with chips. Mix chicken, soups, onions and pepper. Pour over chips, top with cheese. Bake for 25-30 minutes in 350 degree oven.

title: cranberry bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, nuts and softened margarine until well combined.
Add slightly beaten egg, water and flavoring; mix until crumbly.
Pat into bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes until puffed up some, but not brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Grease small casserole dish.
Combine corn, sugar, flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour in pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix in a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in syrup.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in milk, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Bake 50 minutes or until firm.
Cool before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Arrange in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Mix rice, soup (undiluted), onion, milk and cheese.
Spread over broccoli and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: bok choy
directions: Wash and drain bok choy.
Cut in bite sized pieces.
Pour olive oil in wok or skillet and heat.
Saute garlic until slightly brown.
Add bok choy.
Cover and simmer until slightly tender.

title: pork chops and corn dressing
directions: In a large bowl soak bread in milk.
Add cream-style corn, onion, celery, egg, salt and pepper (if desired).
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Fry pork chops (not dry) and stand in dressing sideways.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: spicy hot black-eyed peas
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and saute onions and bell peppers, drain.
Crumble bacon and reserve for later.
Mix remaining ingredients and heat to boiling, then simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour mixture into serving dish; sprinkle with bacon and parsley over top.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix and lightly dress with cole slaw dressing.

title: foolproof bake-a-long custard
directions: Mix eggs, milk powder, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Blend well and stir in hot water.
Pour into custard
cups or large baking dish.
If desired, sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place in pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until a silver knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: antipasto bread
directions: Lay 1 package of crescent rolls out flat on bottom of pan. Then alternate ingredients:
ham, Swiss cheese, salami, Provolone cheese, pepperoni, American cheese, peppers.
Then place on top of that the second crescent rolls (flatten).
Beat eggs with fork. Drizzle over bread into corners.
Cover with aluminum foil at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Remove foil back 1/2 hour at 325°.

title: bacon-water chestnut appetizers
directions: Slice whole chestnuts in 1/2's and soak in bowl of soy sauce 1 hour or more.
Slice bacon into 1/2 strips, longway.
Roll each water chestnut in sugar.
Wrap strip of bacon around and insert toothpick.
Put chestnuts in casserole dish; pour leftover soy sauce on top.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Drain and return to oven 2 to 5 minutes.
Remove from casserole dish to paper towel and then to serving dish.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, salt, sugar and yeast.
Meanwhile, combine milk with oleo, place over heat until almost hot.
Stir into flour mixture and beat until yeast dissolves.
Add eggs, mix well.
Then add enough flour (3 to 4 cups) to make a stiff dough. Let rise until double in bulk.
Then divide dough in halves.
Roll each half in a rectangle.
Spread with melted oleo (1/2 stick), sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar (pecans and raisins may be added at this time).
Roll up as for jelly roll, slice in 1/2-inch slices, place on greased cookie sheet, press each roll flat with palm of hand and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° to 375° until lightly browned.
Ice with butter frosting.

title: marinated pork on skewers
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, mustard, salt, thyme, sage, pepper, garlic and orange peel in plastic container or bag.
Add pork. Close and refrigerate overnight, turning occasionally.
Preheat grill.
Cut orange into 10 wedges, then halve each wedge crosswise; seed.
Thread pork cubes and orange pieces on 6 skewers.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat for 7 to 9 minutes.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Combine.
Drop on cookie sheet, depending on how large you want them.
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: my own lindsay tarts
directions: Cream butter (room temperature) and sugar.
Add almond extract and eggs.
While beating at low speed, slowly add flour and baking powder.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.

title: alabama fresh peach pie
directions: Fill unbaked pie shell with sliced peaches.
Mix egg, sugar, vanilla, and flour.
Drizzle over peaches.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until filling is set and pie crust is done.
Cool.
Serve.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: grandma kline's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and mix well.
Dissolve soda in milk and alternate with flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and mix until smooth.
Spoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cucumber in sour cream(mizeria)
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers very thin; add salt to cucumbers and let stand for 1 hour, then drain liquid.
Add sour cream, sugar, vinegar, pepper and finely chopped onions and mix thoroughly. Serve.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Combine strawberries and 1/2 cup sugar; set aside.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Add eggs, stirring until moistened. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly several times to form a ball.
(Dough will be grainy.)
Press into a wax paper-lined 8-inch round cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden.
Cool in pan on a wire rack and peel off wax paper.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: dessert a la mexi-can caramel flan
directions: Caramelize 1/2 cup sugar by cooking in a large heavy skillet over low heat until melted and golden brown, stirring constantly. While still hot, spread evenly over bottom of a shallow 2-quart casserole.
Cool.

title: gator spread
directions: Chop chicken or crab into small pieces.
You can do this in a food processor or put it through a meat grinder.
Mix with just enough cream cheese to bind it together.
(Bob uses all of the cream cheese.)
Add onions, lemon juice, salt and pepper; mix well.
(Bob also adds some garlic powder.)
Just keep tasting it until it tastes good.

title: beer bread dip
directions: Cut top off loaf of bread (to use as lid).
Dig out bread in chunks; will be used for dipping.
Clean out bread to be used as serving shell; put bread chunks in plastic bag to preserve freshness.
Mix all ingredients well until smooth.
Add beer a little at a time and mix slowly.
Batter should be the consistency of sour cream.
Pour into bread bowl.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients. Cover and chill 2 hours. Stir before serving.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well. Blend in sweet potatoes. Sift dry ingredients together. Add nuts. Stir in creamed mixture alternately with coffee.
Pour batter into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook meat, onion and green pepper until meat is done.
Drain. Add sauce, corn, olives and seasonings.
Simmer 25 minutes.
Add cheese, 6 ounces of sharp Cheddar cheese, shredded; stir until melted.
Turn into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add taco mix.
Prepare according to package directions.
Stir in beans.
Layer mixture with cheese slices and heat 30 minutes at 300°.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheese danish
directions: Cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice together.
Set aside.
Coat 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
On bottom, place 1 package of rolls.
(Just unroll and fit into place).
Layer cream cheese mixture on top of rolls.
Place second package of rolls on top.
Spread egg white on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: buttered bisquets
directions: Pour favorate drink into cup, wait few hours for it to slush.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2 quart casserole, stir together sugar and corn syrup. Cook on high for 4 minutes add peanuts and stir will.
Cook on high 3 to 5 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla and blend well.
Cook on high 2 minutes longer.
Add baking soda. Stir quickly until light and foamy.
Pour into well greased cookie sheet.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes.
When cool, break into small pieces and store in airtight container.

title: red hot chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Saute drained beef with onion, jalapeno and green peppers, 1 tablespoon chili powder and crushed red pepper.
Add water as needed.
Saute for about 10 minutes. Add the beans, tomatoes, Tabasco sauce and remaining chili powder. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Garnish each serving with shredded Cheddar cheese, sour cream or sliced jalapeno peppers, if desired.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook 6 hours on high.

title: spicy cheese mold
directions: Melt cheeses in top of double boiler.
Cook sausage in skillet until brown and crumbly; drain.
Mix cheeses and sausage together. Pour into well-greased Bundt or ring mold.
Chill until firm. Unmold onto serving platter.
Yield:
1 cheese mold.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and make into balls.
Bake about 12 minutes at 425°.

title: ho ho soup with snowflakes(or tremendous tomato soup with rice)
directions: Bring tomatoes to a boil.
Add butter.
Take off heat and add baking soda and sugar.
Heat half and half. Add to tomatoes. Salt and pepper to taste.
If desired, add rice.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients and bake for 15 minutes or serve in chafing dish.

title: baked apples
directions: Wipe and core apples.
Put in a baking dish and fill cavities with sugar and spice, allowing 1/2 cup sugar to 8 apples and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon or nutmeg.
A few drops of lemon juice in boiling water to cover bottom of dish (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 400° until soft.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: pineapple dream cake
directions: Cook vanilla and cut up cream cheese and beat with mixer.
Put drained pineapple in pudding and cream cheese mix.
Spoon over cake.
Put whipped topping on top.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.
Keep refrigerated.
Cut in squares.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
While hamburger is cooking, cook potatoes until totally done.
Then mash potatoes with milk and butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain hamburger and onions; put back in pan.
Put either corn or peas on top of hamburger, then add mashed potatoes.
Then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: denise's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown the first 5 ingredients; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients, adding a couple of tomato paste cans of water.
Let simmer for 30 minutes on low heat.
Remove bay leaves and serve with spaghetti.
Add shredded cheese to sauce, if desired.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Wash fruit.
Cut cored apples and oranges in quarters.
Put fruit through food grinder.
Add sugar to ground fruits and mix well.
Fill jars and refrigerate.

title: taco stew
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a crock-pot and simmer on low all day.
Serve with grated cheese, sour cream and chips on top.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients to melted butter. Crumble over sweet potato mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: velveeta vegetable soup
directions: Bring broth and vegetables to a boil and simmer covered 30 minutes.
Heat soup, cheese, and milk, stirring constantly until cheese is melted.
Add soup mixture to broth and vegetables.
Can be doubled or frozen.

title: nana's zucchini pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an oblong pan.
Mix all the ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into serving pieces.

title: spiced tea
directions: Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls of mix to a cup of hot water; or 3 heaping teaspoonfuls of mix to a mug of hot water.

title: meat loaves
directions: Mix egg, milk, salt and pepper.
Beat slightly.
Add crackers. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape mixture and bake. This recipe makes 4 meat loaves.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage leaves.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain.
Brown meat and season with salt and pepper.
Add onions, rice and eggs.
Roll a portion of filling into each leaf and fasten ends with a toothpick.
Place the cabbage rolls in a baking dish.
Pour soup and water over rolls.
Cover and cook 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cheese cake cupcakes(excellent for parties)
directions: You will need cupcake papers.

title: fred harvey coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage and onion; cover with sugar.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil.
Pour over shredded cabbage and onion.
Let stand at least 4 hours.

title: banana delight pie
directions: Prepare pudding with milk.
Set aside 1 cup filling.
Pour thin layer of remaining filling into cooled pie shell.
Arrange sliced bananas on filling.
Top with rest of filling.
Blend Cool Whip into reserved filling.
Spread over filling.
Chill 3 hours. Garnish as desired.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Mix together Oreos and margarine and place on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese together and spread over cookies.
Mix vanilla pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk and layer over other layers.
Mix chocolate pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk and spread on top of vanilla layer.
Top with 1 (16 ounce) container of Cool Whip.
Chill for 6 hours.

title: crunchy topped squash casserole
directions: Wash squash and trim off ends.
Cook squash and onion in slices in boiling water until tender.
Drain and mash.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in margarine.
Add flour and stir.
Slowly add the melted cheese and all remaining ingredients.
Mix.
Place in a large buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until center begins to bubble.

title: garlic pasta
directions: Heat oleo and olive oil in a saucepan.
Add garlic and heat until garlic turns golden.
Discard garlic.
Set garlic mix aside.

title: brown stew
directions: Brown meat on all sides.
Add water, juice, sauce, garlic, bay leaves and seasoning.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 or 2 hours. Stir so it will not stick.
Remove garlic and bay leaves.
Add veggies; cook until well done.
Thicken for gravy to make 8 to 10 servings.

title: pecan pie surprise bars
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 13 x 9-inch baking pan; reserve 2/3 cup dry cake mix for filling.
In large mixing bowl, combine remaining dry cake mix, butter and 1 egg; mix until crumbly. Press in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until light golden brown.
Meanwhile, prepare filling.
Pour filling over partially baked crust; sprinkle with pecans.
Return to oven and bake 30 to 35 minutes until filling is set.
Cool.
Cut into 36 bars.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruit, such as apple slices, bananas, pineapple, grapes and strawberries.

title: alan's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together in saucepan, bring to a boil.
Great sauce for barbecuing deer steaks, etc.

title: frozen banana-berry parfait
directions: Peel the banana, wrap in a plastic bag and freeze overnight. At serving time, cut banana into 1-inch slices while still frozen. Place it in food processor with the yogurt and honey. Puree, pushing down the sides of the mixture several times with a rubber scraper. Process until the mixture is the consistency of soft-serve ice cream. Spoon mixture into a parfait glass, alternating with layers of fruit. Or spoon into a bowl surrounded by the fruit. Garnish with whole strawberries. Serve immediately. Makes 1 serving.

title: ham and barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in medium sauce pan over medium-high heat.
Add green peppers, onion and garlic, cook stirring often for 2 minutes. Add remaining ingredients, stir to blend well.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: breakfast shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender jar and mix on medium speed until desired consistency is reached.

title: applesauce dump
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in a well buttered greased 2-quart dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: In large pan
mix
corned
beef,
oleo, tomatoes, onion soup, pepper, 2
tablespoons flour and tomato sauce thoroughly and cook slowly; then set aside to cool.
Mix 2 cups flour and shortening with enough water
to
hold
together; mix well and roll out very thin.
Place
dough
in
bottom
of
baking pan; press over bottom and up sides; pour cooked and cooled filling in pan;
then roll out
a
piece
of dough very thin and place over the top of cooked filling.
Bake
at
for about 20 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine soda and buttermilk; set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cream sugar, margarine and shortening.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add buttermilk. Alternate with flour to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Bake in three 9-inch pans in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: demosthenes dip
directions: Heat together soup and jello, stirring until dissolved.
While this cools, chop finely the celery, bell pepper, green onions and pimientos.
Add cream cheese and salad dressing to soup with mixer.
Add salt, Accent and pepper.
Add and fold in vegetables. Refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Mix until well blended.
Serve with gingersnaps.
Keeps well. Makes 7 cups.

title: quick sausage supper
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 10-inch ovenproof skillet, brown sausage and onion.
Drain.
Sprinkle with flour.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, oregano, basil, garlic powder and pepper; mix well. (Also pork and beans, if so desired).
Heat until hot and bubbly, stirring until slightly thickened.

title: quick and easy dip
directions: Mix well and serve with vegetables or chips.

title: chicken-artichoke casserole
directions: Salt, pepper and paprika the chicken pieces.
Brown in 4 tablespoons butter; remove to a casserole dish.
Melt the remaining 2 tablespoons butter in the frying pan; saute mushrooms for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over mushrooms; stir in the chicken bouillon and sherry.

title: baked onions
directions: Place onions in a microwave-safe dish.
Sprinkle with bouillon, garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Dot with margarine. Cover and microwave on High 6 to 7 minutes or until tender, rotating dish a quarter turn after 3 to 4 minutes.

title: orange coconut cookies
directions: Crush wafers.
Add sugar, work in butter.
Mix in orange juice as is (do not add water).
Roll into balls and roll into nuts, if desired.
Place on foil and let them dry out (about 2 hours). Then roll in coconut.
No baking!

title: hot dip
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger until crumbled.
Drain excess fat. Using crock-pot, melt cheese. Add meat, soup, tomatoes, green chilies and onion.
Mix well.
Heat thoroughly. Serve with chips. May also be frozen.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Beat eggs slightly; add coconut, milk and vanilla.
(If time permits, soak coconut in milk several hours to restore moisture.)
Combine with dry ingredients; mix well.
Add melted butter.
Bake in unbaked pastry shell at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add mashed bananas, flour, baking soda and nuts.
Grease and flour 2 (4 x 8-inch) loaf pans.
Pour into pans and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix molasses, powder and water; pour into unbaked pie shells. Mix flour, sugar and butter; top bottoms of pies.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: broccoli-onion casserole(yields 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Place frozen broccoli and water in a 2-quart casserole.
Cook, covered on High for 10 to 11 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Stir to break up.
Stir in onions and soup.
Top with cracker crumbs. Cook on High 5 to 7 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook on High 45 seconds to 1 1/2 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: basic french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Cover and process on whip until well blended.
Chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice
eggplant; cook until tender.
Drain and mash. Add onion, milk and unbeaten eggs.
Melt oleo, then add the crumbs and cheese; mix well. Add half of the cheese mixture to the eggplant.
Pour in casserole dish. Put remaining cheese mixture on top. Bake at 350° until light brown and bubbly. Yields 8 servings.

title: my mother's pie crust
directions: Mix shortening with boiling water, then mix in the milk, salt and baking powder.
Mix in the flour to make crust dough.
Roll out to size pie needed.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Roll out rolls and cover cookie sheet with rolls.
Bake at temperature on package for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: tabouleh
directions: If using raw bulgur, soak 3 hours in boiling water.
Drain. Add salt, lemon juice, chopped scallion, olive oil, garlic and chill in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Add tomato, parsley and mint; place in lettuce-lined bowl.
Trim with crumbled Feta cheese.

title: spicy mexican dip
directions: Combine refried beans, liquid smoke, chili powder and garlic juice.
Place in the bottom of a large bowl.
Mix avocados in a food processor until smooth.
Add chili powder, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Place this mixture on top of the bean mixture.
Place a layer of sour cream on the top of avocado mixture.
Add grated Cheddar cheese, green onions, olives and jalapenos peppers on top. Chopped tomatoes can be added on top also.
Pour taco sauce over top.
Serve with Fritos or Doritos.

title: squash casserole
directions: Steam squash until tender (8 minutes). Drain well.
Mix with next 9 ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix stuffing mix and 1/4 cup margarine.
Put on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked asparagus
directions: In a buttered 9 x 10-inch pan, lay 4 slices of bread and 4 slices of cheese on top and then cover with asparagus and bacon. Lay the last 4 slices of bread on top.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings; beat.
Pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes, until lightly browned.
Serves 4.

title: easy skillet breakfast
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Shred Cheddar.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Boil 1 minute from time it begins a rolling boil.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add lemon juice and bananas and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well. Squeeze out all remaining liquid.
Combine spinach and remaining ingredients.
Mix and shape into balls.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: nancy's barbecue sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan and heat until sugar is dissolved.
This sauce is good on just about anything (chicken, prepared meatballs, spareribs, etc.), whether cooked in oven or on the grill.

title: seafood spread
directions: Combine cheese, sour cream and butter.
Beat until fluffy. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread on bread, bagels or English muffins.
Place on rack in oven.
Toast at medium setting.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, cheese and dry biscuit mix and mix well. Roll into balls the size of a marble.
Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 10 minutes.
Drain off fat after 5 minutes.
These can be frozen after baking and reheated.

title: children's green beans
directions: Cook green beans until done.
Drain off water.
Put in Cheez Whiz; stir up and serve.

title: angel punch
directions: Chill juices almost to freezing.
Combine with other ingredients in punch bowl.
Yields 20 servings.

title: quick fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and milk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Put in pan.

title: mexican fiesta
directions: Simmer 1 to 2 hours.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease a 10-inch Bundt pan.
Allow butter to
soften.
Using an electric mixer, cream butter until fluffy and light yellow.
Slowly add sugar and then eggs one at a time beating continuously.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in small amounts of flour mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into Bundt pan and bake 45 to 60 minutes until cake tester comes out clean.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger slightly and saute onion until clear.
Drain. Spread in 10-inch pie plate.
Cover with cheese.
In separate bowl, mix together milk, eggs, Bisquick or Jiffy, salt and pepper. Pour over hamburger mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean when testing.
Let set 5 minutes before cutting.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Pour
macaroni in and stir until oleo coats it.
Add salt, pepper,
cheese and cold milk. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not stir.

title: crackling cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: italian-style salisbury steaks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, thoroughly combine ground beef, bread crumbs, water, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into 4 oval patties, then place in 1 1/2-quart oblong baking pan.

title: sausage casserole
directions: The night before, line large baking dish with bread.
Pour sausage over bread.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix eggs, milk and mustard together in a separate bowl and beat well.
Pour over sausage and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Mix the biscuit mix, oil, cheese and milk until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously a few seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix margarine and garlic powder.
Brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 12 biscuits.

title: cabbage celery dressing
directions: Boil this for 5 minutes.
Add 1/3 cup Mazola oil.

title: fried rice
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon oil and soy sauce.
Heat wok or skillet. Add oil.
Add egg.
Cook until set.
Turn over.
Remove and dice. Add other tablespoon oil.
Stir-fry green onion and peas for 1 minute.
Add ham, shrimp and rice.
Mix until heated through. Makes 4 servings.
Sprinkle with additional soy sauce when served, if desired.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: potato salsa supreme
directions: Bake washed, pricked potatoes as you normally would.
In a saucepan, add remaining ingredients, except cheese and heat to blend.
When potatoes are done, open the face of each, spoon in the chicken/salsa mix, sprinkle with cheese and place under broiler to have cheese melt (be careful, this happens quickly).

title: strawberry millionaire pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Do not overstir.
Pour mixture into baked pie shell and chill.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs; add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon, beating well after each addition.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Mixture will be very thick.
Press mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Frost when cool with the following frosting.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Drain well.
Cool to room temperature.
Spoon into a large bowl. Add chicken, grapes, water chestnuts and mayonnaise.
Toss gently with fork. Cover and chill.
Just before serving, line dish with lettuce and add cashews.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Boil lasagna noodles until tender.
Noodles should be broken in half.
Combine Sauer's spaghetti sauce mix, water and tomato paste. Over medium heat, heat to boiling, stirring frequently.
Add ground beef to sauce.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat in large pot.
Serve hot.

title: corn bread or johnnycake
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Combine egg, milk and shortening; add to dry ingredients.
Stir lightly; pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: martha washington candy(french bonbons)
directions: Melt oleo.
Pour over coconut.
Add vanilla and Eagle Brand; mix well.
Add pecans and mix well.
Add powdered sugar and mix well, 1/2 box at a time.
Pat out on cookie sheet about 1 inch thick.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Cut into squares, stick a toothpick into each square and dip into Chocolate Dip.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in 3 quarts water with 1 tablespoon salt and pepper until tender.
Remove all except bony pieces.
Sift flour, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt into mixing bowl.
Add 1 cup milk.
Drop from spoon into boiling chicken broth.
Boil uncovered for 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup milk; bring to a boil.
Serve with chicken.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Lightly brown pork chops in skillet.
Place browned pork chops in a single layer in dish.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over the pork chops.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with French bread.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Mix together after noodles and meat have been cooked and drained.
Put in casserole bowl.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: naomi's christmas treats
directions: Mix margarine, brown sugar, coconut and chopped nuts.
Spread over crackers.
Cook at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: wiener schnitzel
directions: Cut off all the fat from meat; pound with meat cleaver and set aside.
Use 3 bowls and fill with: (1) flour, pepper and salt (2) beaten eggs and (3) bread crumbs.

title: gravy icing
directions: Mix milk and flour together and cook.
Let cool.
Add the remaining ingredients; whip until it becomes a smooth fluffy consistency.

title: tohono o'odham white and red bean soup
directions: Boil together until beans and wheat are tender.

title: doctor bird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add bananas, oil, pineapple and juice, vanilla and eggs to dry ingredients.
Stir to blend mixture (do not beat).
Pour into greased angel food cake pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Set aside to cool on a rack without removing from pan.
Serve plain with whipped cream, ice cream or topping of your choice.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in water; add to first ingredients.
Add buttermilk and work together until all the flour is moistened.
Put in a bowl and cover.
Place in refrigerator until ready to use.
Either roll out and cut or place on floured surface and pat out to 1/2 inch thick.
Let rise.
Keep up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: snowball surprise party ball
directions: Combine cheeses until well blended. Add pimiento, green pepper, salt and pepper. Mix well. Gently blend in bacon bits and 1 cup of French fried onions. Shape into ball, roll in remaining onions to coat. Chill until ready to use. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Cook hamburger; drain.
Put into casserole dish.
Cover with onion and mushroom soup.
Spread with shredded cheese over top. Place Tater Tots close together on top of cheese layer.
Cook at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: mom's pumpkin pie(60 year old recipe - circa 1935)
directions: Mix all together and bake for 10 minutes at 425°, then lower the temperature to 350° and bake for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 10 minutes; drain.
Mix soup, Cheese Whiz, and herb packet from stuffing mix.
Brown stuffing in oleo.
Mix broccoli with cheese, soup and herb packet and put in 7 x 13-inch dish.
Put stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: gail's diet cheesecake
directions: The day before, drain yogurt to make yogurt cheese.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease an 8-inch pie pan or 7-inch spring-form pan.
Place yogurt cheese in a medium-size bowl.
