Add sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice and vanilla, mixing gently with a fork until well blended.
Stir in the eggs.
Pour into the prepared pan and smooth the top with a spatula.
Bake until center is set, 20 to 25 minutes for a pie pan or 40 to 45 minutes for a spring-form pan.
Cool slightly on a wire rack.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Make cake and cool.
Mix milk and cream of coconut together. Punch holes all over top of cake.
Pour mixture on cake.
Put 1/2 coconut on top.
Top with Cool Whip.
Put rest of coconut on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Combine the last 5 ingredients and boil 1 minute.
Pour hot over vegetables.
When cool, add one peeled and sliced cucumber.

title: easy chicken cordon bleu
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pound chicken breasts flat; place smooth side down on board and put piece of cheese on each and then a piece of the Prosciutto.
Roll up.
Dip in butter, then in bread crumbs.
Place in buttered casserole and bake for approximately 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Add extra Cool Whip on top if desired. Sprinkle extra blueberries on top for garnish and chill.

title: make your own christmas ornaments
directions: In a saucepan, stir together the baking soda, cornstarch and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is consistency of moist, mashed potatoes.
It will look thin at first, but will get thicker as it cooks.
Turn out on a plate. Cover with damp cloth until cool enough to handle.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut shapes with cookie cutters.
Put small hole at the top of ornaments.
Allow to dry on flat surface overnight.
Paint and decorate.
Protect with glaze.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients in the blender.

title: eagle brand fruit cake
directions: Chop all ingredients as fine as possible and mix thoroughly. Grease pan and use wax paper in pan. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: emerald two-layered gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin with 3/4 cup boiling water.
Cool slightly and beat until light and fluffy.
Fold in whipped topping and cottage cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan; chill until firm.
Dissolve lime gelatin in 1 1/2 cups boiling water and pineapple juice.
Add pineapple, olives and chopped pecans.
Spoon carefully on top of first layer.
Refrigerate and chill overnight.

title: dilly bread
directions: Combine yeast and warm water.
Set aside.
Combine all remaining ingredients together.
Add the softened yeast.
Add 2 1/4 to 2 1/2 cups sifted flour.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size.
Stir dough down.
Turn into well-greased 2-quart casserole. Let rise until light.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with kosher salt.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Fill lightly-greased muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add sour milk.
Fold in apples, nuts and flavoring. Bake in loaf pans at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: crisp swedish sugar cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar, salt, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add the flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Roll in small balls and dip in sugar.
Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: kosher sweet pickles
directions: Boil and pour drained kosher pickles.
Chill in refrigerator a few days.

title: dogfood dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish, spread cream cheese evenly.
Top with chili and put Tabasco on top to desired taste.
Top evenly with cheese.
Bake until warm and cheese is thoroughly melted.
Serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and egg.
Stir into rhubarb and apples. Spoon into pie shell.
Top with lattice crust, crumb crust or my mother's corn flake topping (below).
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: our favorite "family" birthday cake
directions: Night before, combine whipping cream, cocoa and confectioners sugar in beating bowl.
Do not whip, but let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: sauerbraten
directions: In large bowl, combine 3 cups water, vinegar, onions, lemon, sugar, salt, peppercorns, cloves and bay leaves.
Add pot roast, turning to coat with marinade.
Refrigerate for minimum of 4 hours. Remove meat, dry well with paper towels.
Discard lemon, reserve marinade.
Coat meat with 2 tablespoons of flour.
In Dutch oven, over medium heat, brown meat well in margarine.
Add marinade, cover and let simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Remove meat to warm platter, press liquid through coarse sieve and skim off fat.
Measure 4 cups liquid, adding water if necessary.
Return liquid to Dutch oven. Mix remaining 2 tablespoons flour and 1/3 cup water.
Stir into strained liquid; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, add gingersnaps and simmer 3 minutes.
Serve meat thinly sliced with gravy.
Makes 10 servings.

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix corn meal to a paste with one cup cold water.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of the salt to 2 1/2 cups boiling water and stir in corn meal paste.
Slowly cook 1/2 hour.

title: graham toffees
directions: Place crackers in jelly pan lined with foil or on cookie sheet. Combine butter and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil exactly 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add pecans and vanilla. Pour mixture over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 17 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into small pieces.

title: sweet potato pizza
directions: Mix ingredients and press onto round pizza pan.
Crust will be thin. Bake at 325° until light brown.

title: german peach cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar.
Beat well. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add milk.
Blend batter together and pour into square glass pan.
Top with peaches.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
(Can use any fruit.)

title: earthquake cake
directions: Lightly grease (13 x 9-inch) dish/pan or use a nonstick spray. Mix together 1 cup pecans and 1 cup coconut and sprinkle in bottom of dish.
Follow directions on box for preparing cake mix, pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix together cream cheese, butter, powdered sugar and vanilla flavor by hand (do not use mixer). Spoon over top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fresh cranberry pie
directions: Mix together and set aside the fresh cranberries, diced banana and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Cream 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup of sugar together.
Add 2 eggs and beat.
Fold in 1/2 cup pecans (chopped).

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In salad bowl, make a layer of each ingredient.
Seal with Saran Wrap.
Let stand at least 12 hours before serving.
Toss before serving.

title: ripe tomato pickle
directions: Mix tomatoes,
onions and peppers together and then add sugar, vinegar, salt, cinnamon and allspice.
Cook until thick and turns dark. Then put in sterile jars and seal.

title: combination baked beans
directions: Drain beans and pour into a large 3 quart casserole dish. Saute the bacon, drain.
Add onions, sugar, catsup, mustard and vinegar to the drained bacon.
Pour over beans and bake in a 350 oven for 1 hour.
Yield 12 - 15 servings.

title: donuts
directions: Refrigerate overnight.
Fry and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: mother's old fashioned cookies
directions: Add enough flour to be able to roll out and cut in cookie shapes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chantilly salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Add enough water to make 1 cup.
Boil and pour over jello.
Add water, orange juice, lemon juice and salt.
Place in refrigerator.
When syrupy, add fruit and Cool Whip. Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: tortilla pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add the rest of ingredients, saving 1/2 cup of water to mix with flour.
Cook until done.
In large pan, place a layer of the cooked ground beef mixture; then a layer of cheese, then tortillas . Repeat until pan is full, ending with cheese on top.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: taco burger
directions: Crush 1/3 corn chips.
Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Fix in beef patties and broil over grill.
Take cream cheese and cut into 12 strips 1/8-inch thick.
Lay 2 cheese strips across each burger patty and sprinkle with paprika and roll.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in small baking pan.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes in rounds and boil until almost done.
Drain and put potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Salt and pepper to taste. Melt butter in a large skillet; add onion and saute until tender. Add the milk and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Pour over potatoes and bake about 20 minutes.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a 3-quart saucepan over very low heat, melt butter and chocolate, stirring the mixture constantly.
Remove pan from heat and with a spoon, stir the sugar into the chocolate.
Allow the mixture to cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until well blended after the addition of each egg.
Add the flour, vanilla and salt to the mixture and stir in well.
Add the chopped nuts to the mixture and stir well.
Pour chocolate nut mixture into greased baking pan.
Bake in oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: nutty yam bake
directions: Bake sweet potatoes. Mash while hot. Add sugar, butter and spices. Mix well. Beat in eggs and milk. Whip with mixer. Turn into 3-quart greased casserole.

title: cranberry orange relish or salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add spices and cranberry sauce.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in oranges and apples.
Pour into 6-cup mold or bowl.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Serve as salad or relish.
Makes about 5 cups or 10 side salads or 14 relish servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in a 4-cup Pyrex measuring cup.
Cook 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook 1 minute.
Add soda.
Quickly stir and pour into buttered pan.
When cool, break into small pieces and store in airtight container.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until creamy.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add to the mixture.

title: baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Saute green pepper and onion together. Mix all ingredients, except bacon.
Place in a 2-quart casserole. Add bacon on top.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: easy german chocolate cake
directions: Melt 1/2 cup oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans over oleo.
Mix cake mix according to directions on the box.
Pour over the nuts.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1/2 cup oleo.
Dip by spoonfuls onto cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pistachio nut dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and sugar together with nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes; cool. Combine cream cheese, 10x sugar and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread over bottom layer in pan.
Mix pudding with milk and stir until thickened.
Spread over layer.
Use remaining Cool Whip to cover pudding and sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.
Serves 15.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Wash raisins in warm water.
Drain well.
Into a large bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and pepper. Cut in butter as for pie dough.
Mix in raisins.
Add egg to buttermilk; mix well and stir into flour mixture.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board.
Knead lightly (about a minute).
Do not overwork.
Shape into a round cake and place in greased 10-inch pan (iron if possible).
Cut cross on top and prick surface with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes longer.
When done, brush with butter.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add shortening, lemon and orange rinds, orange juice and eggs.
Mix until blended.
Fold in nuts and berries.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Press into corners, leaving a slight hollow in the center.
Set aside for 20 minutes.
Preheat the oven to 350°. Bake 60 to 70 minutes.

title: spinach spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: candlestick bars
directions: Combine gingerbread mix and applesauce.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed with electric mixer or 2 minutes with spoon.
Stir in raisins and fruits and peels.
Spread in greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Prepare frosting according to package directions, substituting the lemon juice for half the liquid.
Spread on cooled cookies.
Cut in 1 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Decorate with candlesticks made from gumdrops.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: delicious dip
directions: Drain juice from can of crab meat.
Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with Fritos or tortilla chips.
Keep refrigerated.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Shred cabbage; add chopped pepper and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix vinegar, oil and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Layer cabbage, onion and pepper and pour vinegar over it.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Stir well at this time.

title: frosted orange creme
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend well; serve at once.
Makes 3 cups or 2 servings.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Drain shrimp and soften cream cheese.
Mix together in blender. Serve on lettuce leaves with cocktail sauce poured over top. (Homemade sauce is ketchup, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce.) Spread is good served with Triscuit crackers.

title: butterscotch delights
directions: Melt morsels in top of double boiler, do not boil.
Remove from heat and stir in pecans and noodles.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Chill 10 minutes.
Store in airtight container and will keep for days.

title: dosas(indian flat bread)
directions: Combine cornmeal, whole wheat flour, all-purpose flour and salt.
Add rice, milk and water.
Stir to mix; cover bowl and set aside for at least an hour.
Spray griddle with nonstick spray. Heat and pour on about 1/4 cup of batter.
Cook until one side is brown and batter has holes in it; turn and cook other side.
If necessary, turn again to dry out first side.
Eat warm or cool. Yields 12 flat breads.

title: my grandfather's famous frogmore stew
directions: Bring a large kettle of water to boil.	Add sausage and Old Bay seasoning and boil for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and boil with sausage for 15 to 20 minutes more.
Add corn.
Boil with sausage and potatoes for another 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and drain immediately.
Serve on a large platter.

title: white chocolate raspberry bars
directions: Grease and flour 9-inch baking pan.
Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat and add 1 cup chopped white chocolate.
Do not stir.
Set aside and let it stand.

title: grilled salmon steaks
directions: Combine all ingredients, except fish.
Pour into a covered dish.
Add fish.
Marinate 1 to 2 hours, turning twice.
Place on grill and bake 4 to 6-inches from coals, 10 to 12 minutes, turning once.
Brush frequently with marinade.

title: pudding poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box for 9 x 13 pan.
Bake as directed.
Poke holes with a round handle wooden spoon about 1-inch apart.
After the holes are made, combine sugar and pudding in bowl.
Gradually add milk.
Beat with mixer for 1 minute.
Do not overbeat.

title: ham puffs
directions: Combine
butter, cheese, ham and seasonings.
Add flour and shape into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Yield:
50 puffs.
(Freezes well.)

title: harolyn's peach ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients on medium speed until peaches are small bits. Pour into freezer.

title: brown rice
directions: Put everything in casserole dish and stir (leave dish uncovered).
Bake at 350°; it takes about as long as chicken does (approximately 40 minutes).
For 2 people, half all ingredients.

title: lemon butter quicky
directions: Melt butter.
Combine all of the ingredients in saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full bubbling boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/2 pints.
Good on toast and English muffins.

title: peach pie
directions: Cook 2 cups of the peaches with water, sugar and cornstarch. Cook until thick.
Cool and add lemon juice.
Add remaining 2 cups of peaches and put in a baked crust.
Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: microwave pasta primavera
directions: Microwave cream cheese and margarine on High for 5 minutes, until just to boil.
Pour over hot broccoli and pasta.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Toss rhubarb and strawberries in bowl with flour, sugar and salt.
Let stand about 20 minutes.
Prepare 9-inch pie crust. Pour fruit mixture into unbaked pie crust.
Dot with butter.
Mix milk and egg together.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 375° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: braised beef with noodles
directions: Roll meat in flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown in heated cooking oil, using only enough to prevent sticking in pan.
May only need 1/2 amount listed.
Put meat in roasting pan.
Cut onion in eighths, add to meat.
Add V-8 juice, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Add peas and cook 10 more minutes.
Serve over cooked, buttered noodles.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 4.

title: ann street's homemade chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onions, and garlic.
Drain excess fat. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Stir and simmer about 30 minutes. Makes about 4 servings (2/3 cup each).

title: key lime pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat condensed milk and egg yolks until light and creamy (about 8 minutes).
Add lime juice; mix on low speed for a few seconds. Fold mixture a few times with a rubber spatula to be sure juice is thoroughly blended.
Pour mixture into baked pie crust.
Let stand.
With electric mixer, beat egg whites with cream of tartar for 5 minutes.
Add sugar; beat 5 minutes more.
Cover pie with meringue, making sure to seal meringue to edge of crust.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 10 minutes, or until the meringue is golden brown.

title: "easy brunswick stew"
directions: Cook tomatoes a few minutes. Add corn, peas and meat. Mix well. Simmer all on low heat or simmer low in crock-pot for 2 to 3 hours. Serve with corn bread.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil 9 minutes stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, vanilla and pecans.
Pour onto waxed paper.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Perfect every time.

title: cheese log
directions: Cream all together and shape into a log.
Roll log in chopped nuts, chives, parsley or whatever to completely cover.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Add to all other ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pecan balls
directions: Mix and make small balls.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: chicken-macaroni casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Turn into shallow glass casserole dish, 13 x 8 1/2-inches.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or use two smaller casserole dishes.

title: holly's dinner rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Scald milk and add sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool mixture to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups of flour and beat well.
Add softened yeast and eggs.
Mix well and add the remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on floured board or countertop and knead until smooth and satiny.

title: golden sauce
directions: Stir the Velveeta cheese and milk in a saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Serve over hot pasta, vegetables, etc.

title: cinnamon pudding
directions: Bring 2 cups brown sugar, water and 2 tablespoons butter to a full boil; let cool.
Beat remaining ingredients, except pecans, until well blended.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle nut meats over dough.
Then pour 1st mixture over dough.
Bake at 325° until dough rises to top and comes out clean when pierced with toothpick.
Cool before serving.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: mother's stew
directions: Brown meat and add remaining ingredients into greased large casserole dish or Dutch oven.
Bake, covered, at 250° for 5 hours.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Beat eggs together.
Add all other ingredients to beaten eggs.
Refrigerate overnight in a covered bowl.
The next day, pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar and salt.
Add all milk, adding whole milk last to complete filling the freezer can.
Chill until ready to freeze.

title: potatoes in sour cream
directions: Scrub potatoes and cook in boiling, salted water.
Drain, then peel and slice into a 2-quart baking dish.
Melt butter in a skillet.
Add onion and brown slightly.
Add onion, bread crumbs and cheese to potatoes.
Beat eggs and stir into sour cream.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until well heated and slightly brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: roger staubach's spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach; remove stems.
Tear in bite-size pieces.
In a tall bottle, mix dry ingredients first, then add liquid ingredients, mixing well.
Put onion in for flavor, but remove at serving.
Makes enough dressing for 2 bags of spinach.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Mix additional ingredients and store in covered container overnight.

title: layered toffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream just until it begins to thicken. Gradually add the ice cream topping and vanilla, beating until soft peaks form. Cut cake horizontally into 3 layers. Place the bottom layer on a serving plate. Spread with 1 cup cream mixture and sprinkle with 1/2 cup Heath bits. Repeat. Place top layer on cake; frost top and sides with remaining cream mixture and sprinkle with remaining Heath bits. Store in refrigerator.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix
all ingredients well;
form into small cakes.
Fry in 1/4-inch hot oil until brown.
Makes 14 cakes.

title: peach cobbler #1
directions: Mix margarine, 1/2 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk; spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour peaches on top of mixture.
Sprinkle peaches with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave english muffin pizza
directions: Pour sauce and sprinkle cheese on pizza.
Microwave on High for 30 seconds.

title: strawberry angel cream
directions: Combine Jell-O and boiling water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add strawberries without thawing.
Stir until thawed.
Chill until begins to congeal.
Break cake into golf-ball sized pieces into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Reserve 1 cup strawberry Jell-O mixture; blend 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip with rest of strawberry mixture.
Decorate top by spooning reserved cup of Jell-O mixture over top in marbleizing effect.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Top with Cool Whip. Yield:
12 servings.

title: lazy cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and butter in pan.
Bring to boil and cook 1 minute.
Take off heat; add the remaining ingredients and mix.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan with butter.
Pour mixture in pan and let cool.
Cut in squares.

title: little pizzas
directions: Fry sausage; drain thoroughly.
Return to pan.
Cut up Velveeta in skillet and melt with sausage.
Spread mixture on rye bread slices and sprinkle with oregano.
To serve, bake until lightly browned and cheese is hot.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Mix with celery, onions, mayonnaise and cheese.
Mix cracker crumbs and melted margarine; place on top of vegetable mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: "mamma's" lemon cream pie
directions: Combine flour and 1 1/4 cups of sugar in top of double boiler; add water, stirring constantly, then add milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour small amount of mixture over egg yolks, stirring vigorously.
Return to double boiler and continue cooking until mixture drops in thick sheets from spoon. Add butter, lemon juice and rind.
Cool and pour into pie shell.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding, milk, and sugar with a whisk or on slow speed of mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In GLASS 9 x 13 inch pan, layer graham crackers on bottom.
Top with half of pudding mixture.
Put another layer of grahams.
Layer remaining pudding and then another layer of graham crackers.
Top all with chocolate frosting, sealing edges.
(Or frosting may be heated for 45 seconds in the microwave and poured on top.)
Refrigerate 8 hours before serving.

title: chili powder
directions: Grind and combine all ingredients into sealed spice container. Use less of this powder than anything you'll buy!
This is super flavorful and concentrated.
Will change the way you've been tasting your favorite Mexican dishes.

title: banana jam
directions: Squeeze limes and set aside.
Peel and slice bananas 1/4-inch thick.
Pour lime juice over bananas; stir and set aside.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients (in powdered form) in a large bowl thoroughly.
Store in an airtight container until ready to use. Add 2 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.
Makes 40 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in punch bowl.
Use ice or a frozen juice ring made out of Five-Alive juice.

title: pizza in a burger
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and pepper.
Shape into patties and broil 5 to 6 minutes. Turn and top with cheese and tomatoes.
Let broil 5 minutes.
Serve on toasted buns.

title: gypsy schnitzel(zigeunerschnitzel)
directions: Sprinkle steaks with salt and pepper; dip into egg mixture and bread crumbs.
Fry in shortening until brown on both sides. Remove pork chops or pork steaks.
Add onion and peppers to drippings and saute a couple of minutes.
Add mushrooms, water and the bouillon cube; bring to a boil.
Make a paste with the cornstarch and a tablespoon of cold water.
Pour into the sauce and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Season with salt, paprika and chili powder to taste.
Add pork chops or pork steaks. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes and serve.
Serves 4.

title: french market soup
directions: Soak soup beans overnight with salt.
Drain and add water, ham hock, bay leaf and thyme. Cover and simmer for 3 hours.
Add tomatoes, onions, celery, green pepper, garlic and red pepper. Simmer 1
1/2 hours, uncovered. Add chicken and smoked sausage. Ten minutes before serving, add parsley.

title: oriental cole slaw
directions: Mix together cole slaw and onions.
Brown sesame seed and sliced almonds in a small amount of oil; cool.
Blend sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Break Ramen noodles on top of cole slaw (do not use seasonings).
Pour on dressing.
Add seeds and nuts.
Needs to set at least 2 hours.
Toss just before serving.

title: dried apple roll
directions: Cook apples until soft; stir in sugar.
Make a crust from any recipe.
Roll dough out in rectangle about 1/4 inch thick.
Put cooked apples on top of crust.
Starting at long edge, roll up like jelly roll and transfer to a greased baking sheet.
Pinch edges together good and lay seam side down.
Sprinkle with sugar and butter.
Cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve with Mama (Lena) Rohrer's Sauce.

title: old fashion coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well; add dry ingredients which have been sifted together, alternately with milk and beat on slow speed for 2 minutes. Add 3 eggs, unbeaten, and vanilla. Beat on slow speed for 2 minutes. Bake in 3 well greased layer pans at 350° for about 20 or 25 minutes. When cake layers are cool, ice with the following Divinity Icing.

title: squash dressing
directions: Add all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Sprinkle ham, onion and cheese into the bottom of pie shell. In blender, mix eggs, half and half and seasonings.
Blend on high until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.

title: white bean chicken chili
directions: Put chicken broth, beans and salsa in crock pot.
Pull apart chicken and add to pot.
Then add grated cheese.
Cook 1 hour on high and 4 hours on low in crock pot.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan 2 cups crushed pretzels, 3/4 cup melted margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix and drop in broth.
Don't uncover for 12 minutes.

title: cracker dip
directions: Mix together in a large bowl.
Serve with Hi Ho crackers.

title: key lime pie
directions: Slowly add lime juice to condensed milk.
Beat until blended. Add cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate until sets up.
Garnish with lime peel.

title: roasted peanuts
directions: Place peanuts in
shallow
pan.
Place pan in 325° oven and allow to roast for ten minutes, stirring often.
After ten minutes, turn oven	off
and
let peanuts remain in oven until oven cools.

title: crab cakes
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Stir in flour and mix well. Add slowly the milk.
Keep stirring until smooth.
Add crab spice. Remove from burner and gently add crabmeat.
Chill for 1 hour or more. Shape into 6 to 8 oval cakes.
(Wet your hands to make it easier.)
Roll in fine bread crumbs (with lemon and pepper seasoning, optional).
Fry in heated pan or deep fry. Drain and serve.

title: sausage and ham jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage and ham in Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook uncovered for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes adding additional water if necessary.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: german-style potato supper
directions: In large skillet, brown sausage.
Stir in potatoes, 3/4 cup water and bouillon; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over meat mixture; simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes or until thick and bubbly.
Serve immediately.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 4.

title: yellow party punch
directions: Makes approximately 40 punch cups full.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together with hands.
Shape into balls.
Bake on cookie sheet 20 to 30 minutes, at 350°.
Serves 60 small balls.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper, celery and garlic in margarine. Add crab boil, tomatoes, tomato sauce, water and bay leaves. Simmer before adding shrimp; add shrimp and additional water to desired consistency.
Cook until shrimp are tender, about 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken in melted margarine; coat with cracker mixture.
Place chicken in baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook peppers until tender.
Place in baking dish.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix cooked rice, browned ground beef, onion and tomatoes together.
Stuff peppers first, then pour the rest on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cut chicken in chunks.
Let stand in 6 tablespoons soy sauce for 30 minutes.
Dip chicken in egg.
Roll in cornstarch.
Fry in oil.
Add soup and soy sauce mixture.
Add water and cashews. Simmer 15 minutes, covered.

title: chocolate chip peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter and margarine.
Add the sugars and cream well.
Add the eggs and vanilla.
Add the flour, soda and salt. Add the chips last.
Drop with teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Beat together pudding mix and milk for 2 minutes. Stir in Cool Whip. Butter 9 x 13 baking dish. Put 1 layer of graham crackers in bottom of dish. Pour 1/2 pudding mixture over crackers. Put another layer of crackers, then the other 1/2 of pudding mixture. Top with graham crackers. Spread 1 container of chocolate fudge frosting over graham crackers. Refrigerate 24 hours. Enjoy!

title: yum-a-setta(an amish dish)
directions: Brown meat with onion; add brown sugar and tomato soup.
Cook noodles in water; drain.
Add cream of chicken soup to noodles. Layer meat mixture and noodle mixture in casserole.
Add cheese between the mixture.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.
I like to add diced peppers and dry basil.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Parboil chicken; skin and bone.
Place chicken pieces in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Mix soup, wine, mushrooms and sour cream. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: smyzences
directions: Mix the first four ingredients together. Add enough flour to make it stiff. Chill, roll out in flour. Cut into strips. Drop in hot oil. Cook until golden brown.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, beat brown sugar, oil and egg well.
Add flour, buttermilk, salt, soda, cinnamon and vanilla. Beat on low speed until mixed well.
Fold in rhubarb and nuts. Pour mixture into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon butter, mixed until crumbly.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes or until done.
Wrap and store overnight to develop flavor.
Slices easier the next day too.

title: burger and eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant until skin is tender; peel and slice.
Set one sliced eggplant aside.
Place other slices of eggplant in a saucepan; add 1 1/2 cups water and chicken style seasoning.
Let boil until tender or very soft.
Mash eggplant and set aside.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt.
Add unbeaten egg whites and almond extract.
Drop onto greased cookie sheets and bake at 350° until golden brown.
Remove from pan immediately or they will stick.

title: company's coming cashew pie
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
In a large bowl, beat brown sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add corn syrup and vanilla. Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Beat in eggs one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Stir in cashew nuts.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until top of pie is deep golden brown.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Layer cabbage, green peppers and onions in bowl; do not mix. Cook remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour hot dressing over vegetables.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
This will keep in the refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: coconut pie
directions: In a blender; combine first seven ingredients. Cover and blend for 10 seconds; scrape sides. Blend another 10 seconds. Add coconut; blend for 2 seconds Pour into greased 10 inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 50 - 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Serve warm.

title: avocado appetizers
directions: Mix shrimp, mayonnaise, parsley and salt.
Cut avocados in half and remove stones.
Spoon shrimp mixture onto avocado.
Top with cheese.
Place under broiler.
Cook just until cheese melts, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Slowly add to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls and put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool slightly before moving from pan.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: cheater's chowder
directions: Fry the chopped bacon and onion together until the onion is soft.
Prepare soup according to directions on can.
Add the clams, bacon, onion and pepper; simmer 12 minutes and serve with a dab of butter floating in the middle.
Serve with salad and French bread.
Serves two.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine instant pudding and milk, mixing until smooth.
Add sour cream and 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Beat until all blended in. Alternate mixture between layers of vanilla wafers and bananas.

title: pecan loaf
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Beat eggs with milk.
Mix all ingredients and pour into oiled casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Soften
the
gelatin in the cold water; mix in the sugar and boiling water until dissolved; stir in the lemon juice and rind. Chill
until syrupy but don't let it set.
Since texture will
not be smooth.
Beat the salt and egg whites until stiff, but
not dry.
Gradually add the corn syrup, beating steadily. Fold
the lemon
mixture
into the egg whites.
Chill about 20 minutes, stirring
occasionally.
Mixture should be set enough to
be
able to
heap it.
Spoon into the pie shell until set. Serves
8. Calories:
per
serving.
Low
salt
and
low cholesterol.

title: cool pie
directions: Dissolve Jello in boiling water. Gradually add ice cream, stirring until melted. Then chill until thickened, but not set - 15 to 20 minutes.
Fold in strawberries. Pour into crumb crust. Chill until firm. Top with Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: tony's brownies
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and vanilla.
Melt shortening with chocolate. Sift flour and baking powder together.
Combine ingredients and add nuts.
Place in 8 x 8 greased pan and bake at 350° for 20-30 minutes.

title: leek tarte(tarte aux poireaux)
directions: Steam the leeks in a covered skillet for 10 minutes with the butter.
Beat the eggs.
Add salt and heavy cream.
Fit puff pastry into a 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle cheese on bottom; cover with prepared leeks.
Pour egg mixture over leeks.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: party broccoli
directions: Saute one large onion in butter.
Add frozen broccoli, cheese, mushrooms and salt and pepper to taste to onion mixture.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Pour cooked mixture into casserole dish; sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: blueberry cheese pie
directions: In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in milk until smooth. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into crust and chill for 3 hours. Top with blueberry pie filling.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla.
Boil for 3 minutes. Remove and add vanilla.
If too thick when cool, add a little milk.
Keeps well in refrigerator.
Heat in microwave for a hot syrup again.
Delicious on ice cream!

title: quick fish chowder
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add fish and cook until done.
Add soup and milk and heat until hot.
Do not boil.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in butter.
Toss together lightly the cornbread crumbs and squash.
In a separate bowl, mix soup and milk well.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased or buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir together, blending well, refrigerate.

title: chicken fantastic
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon margarine and pour over stuffing mix.
Stir together cream of celery soup and mayonnaise.
Mix all ingredients together except for the stuffing mix.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: light fruitcake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine walnuts, cherries, pineapple and raisins.
Toss with the 1 cup flour; set aside.
Cream together margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well between each addition.
Stir in lemon extract. Sift together the 2 cups of flour and the baking powder.
Add in thirds to the creamed mixture; mix well.
Add batter to fruit, mixing well to coat all the fruits and nuts.
Transfer batter to a well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Place a pan of hot water on bottom rack.
Bake cake on shelf above water in a 300° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Remove foil; bake 20 minutes longer or until top is slightly dry.
Remove cake from pan when cooled thoroughly.
Store in tightly covered container.
Will keep for months well-wrapped and in the refrigerator.

title: chinese chicken salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients except chips and almonds.
Refrigerate overnight to bring out flavor.
Poach 1 chicken breast.
Shred; set aside.
Prepare tossed salad, using your favorite vegetables. Spread shredded chicken on vegetables.
Sprinkle almonds and won ton chips.
Serve with prepared dressing.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add shortening and the first amount of milk called for.
Beat with mixture for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, rest of milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Boil.
Remove from heat for 5 minutes.
Pour Certo and food coloring into mixture.
Bring to boil for 1 minute and pour into jars while hot.
Cap jars and refrigerate.
When cool, excellent served over cream cheese with wheat crackers.

title: sweet potato nut bread
directions: Cream butter and oil together.
Add sugar and eggs.
Blend in sweet potatoes.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix with nuts. Add to creamed mixture.
Mix in coffee.
Pour into 2 loaf pans. Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: fat-free banana bread
directions: In a bowl, combine salt, flour, baking powder and soda.
In another bowl, combine sugar, 1/2 cup applesauce and egg whites. Beat vigorously until frothy.
Add bananas and blend thoroughly. Fold into flour mixture until blended.

title: zucchini cupcakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, sugar, oil, orange juice and extract.
Combine dry ingredients; add to the egg mixture and mix well.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups two-thirds full. Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes or until cupcakes test done.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack.
Cool and frost.

title: double-lime punch
directions: Combine in punch bowl and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Cook broccoli by box instructions. Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fantastic green beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook for 4 hours.
Stir often, cooking the water out completely, then you're ready to serve.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Let cool.
Mix pineapple and pie filling with Jell-O.

title: "aunt maggie's" muffins
directions: Combine water and raisins and bring to a slow boil (approximately 20 minutes).
Add dates and cool.
Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add fruit and liquid.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Combine mixtures.
Do not overmix.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pickled peppers
directions: Toss sliced peppers with pickling salt and set overnight. Rinse and drain peppers.
Combine vinegar, water and sugar in a large pan and bring to a boil.
Put peppers into hot jars.
Pour boiling liquid in to fill jars almost to the top.
Seal jars. Yields 3 quarts or 6 pints.

title: yellow cake from scratch
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and salt.
Add in eggs, then add flour one cup at a time.
Finally, add milk and vanilla.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 300°.

title: taco casserole(microwave)
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Add meat to the tomato sauce, beans and seasoning mix.
Pour over 2 cups corn chips in bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Put in microwave for 7 to 8 minutes on High.
Sprinkle the remaining chips over the top.
Add cheese, heat until cheese melts.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: pumpkin pie(10-inch)
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Line bottom of pie crust with marshmallows, then pour in pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 50 minutes longer until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mexican tea cakes
directions: Combine flour, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Add butter, pecans, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and vanilla. Stir until well blended. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while hot. Cool on wire racks. Re-roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Pat softened cream cheese on bottom of deep microwave dish. Spread chili on top, then top with cheese.
When ready to serve, microwave until cheese melts.
Dip with tortilla chips.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour, then slowly add cream and stir constantly until thickened.
Stir in catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Add shrimp and crab and stir gently over low heat until through.
Season with salt, paprika and cayenne pepper.

title: blueberry pie(diabetic)
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup soda; set aside.
Crush 1 cup blueberries in top of double boiler and cook with 1 cup soda.
Add lemon juice, butter flavoring, cinnamon and sweetener.
Cook 10 minutes.
Fold in 2 cups blueberries.
Pour into chilled pie plate.
Chill.

title: atsuko's oriental chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients in a Ziploc bag, then add chicken. Marinate overnight.
Bake on baking rack at 350°.
Turn chicken once.
Cook until chicken becomes golden brown or great for barbecuing.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Glaze as soon as it is removed from oven.
Remove from pan to cool after letting set 10 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water to 230°.
Add peanuts and boil to 310° or hard crack.
Remove from heat.
Mix in vanilla, butter and soda.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix soup and mayonnaise together in a bowl; set aside.
Layer items in casserole dish in the following order:
rice, broccoli, chicken, sauce and cheese.
Put in oven uncovered; bake until cheese melts.
Then cover and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until hot.
Serve hot and enjoy!

title: crackly corn
directions: Put popped corn in large greased pan.
Combine sugar, butter, corn syrup, salt and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour over corn. Stir to coat well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes while baking.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: tingalings
directions: Mix together and form into balls.

title: slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and onion and place in a large bowl. In Combine rest of ingredients EXCEPT for oil in a cooking pan. Bring to a boil.
Add cooking oil and heat to a boil. Cool. Pour over cabbage and onion. Let set one hour or more.

title: bread dressing for fowl
directions: Saute giblets in butter.
Remove giblets and saute onions. Combine with remaining ingredients.
Bake in a shallow pan until browned.

title: yogurt tomato cocktail
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shake briskly and chill until ready to serve.

title: cheese noodle ring
directions: Saute in small pan with olive oil on low setting 10 minutes. Add to black beans; stir well.
Add water if needed.
Add 2 tablespoons white vinegar and stir.
Let set 30 minutes on low. Cooked beans to be served over rice.
Sprinkle with finely chopped onions if desired.
Leftover beans may be cooled and frozen for use with another meal.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Quickly fry 1 tortilla at a time in hot oil (375°) to soften.
Spoon a heaping tablespoonful of chicken mixture onto each; spread down center and roll.
Place, seam side down, in an oiled 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon over green chilies.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and enchiladas are hot.
Serve with lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream and guacamole or chopped avocados.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Coat chicken in flour.
Heat oil in large skillet until hot. Add chicken and cook for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring and turning 2 to 3 times until chicken is golden on all sides.
Remove to a small bowl.
Pour water in skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice, seasonings and peas.
Cover; simmer for 18 to 20 minutes, until most of the liquid is absorbed.
Stir in chicken and pimientos. Cook an additional 3 minutes or until water is absorbed and chicken is white in center.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Mix all well.
Add 2 packages of the diced ham; mix well. Now, roll into ball and roll ball in a third package of diced ham. Chill and serve on crackers.
Serves 10 people.

title: baked cheese goodies
directions: You work the cheese and flour together until crumbly with your hands.
Add butter and mix well with a fork.
If the dough seems dry, work it with your hands.
Mold 1 teaspoon of dough around the sausage and shape into a ball.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Chill for 1 hour.
Then bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 400° oven.
These can be frozen.

title: new orleans' dreams
directions: Put sugar, corn syrup, salt and milk in saucepan.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boiling point and boil until a little dropped in cold water will hold its shape like putty or clay, a firm hard ball.
Let stand 10 minutes, then add nuts. Beat vigorously until thick and creamy.
Drop onto oiled paper by teaspoon.

title: fried rice
directions: In a large skillet or wok, fry up bacon.
Set aside.
Remove all but 1 tablespoon oil.
Scramble eggs.
Chop up onions (green tops included).
Place all ingredients in wok.
Stir-fry for 5 minutes.
Season with Kikkoman soy sauce.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onions.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart dish.
Cover. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Split green peppers lengthwise into halves.
Remove seeds, stems and membranes.

title: glazed meat loaf
directions: Dice onion, celery and garlic; peel and dice carrots and 1 teaspoon dried thyme, crumbled.
Cook veggies until tender.
Mix next four ingredients and save 1/2 for top.
Mix other ingredients and add veggies and 1/2 sugar mixture.
Top with remaining sugar mixture.
Bake in two small loaf pans and bake at 350° about 1 hour or until done.

title: louisiana jambalaya
directions: Brown meat in bacon drippings; remove and add flour.
Brown flour to a dark roux.
Add onion, parsley and garlic; cook until soft, then add water, rice, salt and pepper and browned meat. When it comes to a boil, lower heat to lowest point; cook for 1 hour covered tight.
When rice is done, remove lid and let cook few more minutes until rice dries a little.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spareribs aloha
directions: Cut after every third rib, about 1/2 way through it.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and place in a shallow roasting pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/4 hours.
Carefully pour off excess fat.
While ribs are roasting, mix remaining ingredients and let stand to blend flavor.
Pour over ribs after 1 1/4 hours baking. Bake 45 to 50 minutes longer, basting frequently to glaze ribs with the sauce.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Have ready peanut butter and quick oatmeal.
Boil sugar, butter, milk, vanilla and cocoa for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; dissolve peanut butter and add oatmeal.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper; let cool.

title: meat loaf italiano
directions: Combine bread crumbs and milk.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Mix lightly with ground beef, 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce and seasoning until well blended.
Put half in 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pan.

title: pickled dilled beans
directions: Wash beans; drain.
Trim ends.
Cut beans to fit jars.
Cover beans with boiling water; cook 3 minutes.
Pack lengthwise into hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
In saucepan, combine vinegar, 3 cups water, pickling salt, dill weed, cayenne and garlic.
Bring to boil.
Cover beans with pickling liquid, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath pints and quarts 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Grease 8-inch square pan.
Mix soup, onions and water.
Layer 1/3 broccoli, 1/3 soup mix, 1/3 stuffing and 1/3 margarine until all is used.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together, then add hot water slowly.
Cook until thickness desired.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Serve with plain cake and ice cream.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except poppy seed in blender or covered container. Cover and blend or shake until thoroughly mixed.
Stir in poppy seed.
Chill before serving with fresh fruit in season.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger with onion, pour off the grease.

title: haystacks
directions: Put peanut butter and chips into a double broiler. Place over hot water until melted. Mix well. Add noodles; mix well. Drop by spoonfuls on to cookie sheets lined with wax paper. Cool.

title: taco dip
directions: Stir-fry hamburg with taco seasoning mixed in.
Add 1/2 jar salsa to sour cream.
Top with remaining hamburg mixture.
Mix in cheese.
Top with remaining salsa sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mock heath bar
directions: Line a 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet (with edge) with foil.
Cover bottom with soda crackers (single layer).
In saucepan, combine brown sugar, margarine and butter.
Heat and bring to boil (rolling boil).
Allow to boil 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers. Place in oven preheated to 400° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate tidbits over top.
As they soften, lightly spread chocolate to edges.
Place pan in refrigerator for approximately 3 hours.
Peel off foil and break up like chocolate bark.
Use enough foil to extend over edge of pan and then lift out of pan in one piece.
It's a winner every time!!

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually stir in pineapple and 1/2 cup nuts, green pepper, onions and salt. Shape into a ball.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate overnight or until well chilled.
Serve with crackers.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and oleo. Mix well, stir in oats.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sunday dinner green bean casserole
directions: Put in a large casserole dish.
Drain beans; layer 2 cans, 1 can cream of mushroom soup, 1 can of French fried onions, then repeat and top with butter.
Cook at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: red apple inn chicken
directions: Wrap bacon around each 1/2 chicken breast.
Lay 1 slice dried beef over each breast.
Arrange in baking dish.
Mix until well blended, cream cheese, sour cream and mushroom soup.
Spoon over chicken breast.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours in covered dish or foil covered pan or dish.
Uncover for about 30 minutes of baking time to let brown.

title: tomato-cheese soup
directions: Turn soup into a large saucepan; gradually blend in milk. Stir until hot and blended.
Mix in cheese and, if desired, basil.

title: fudge pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour together.
Melt butter and chocolate together; add vanilla and salt.
Combine mixtures; stir and pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until pie springs back when touched in the middle.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
This pie is quite rich, so helping can be small.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash together the avocado and Ricotta cheese.
Fold in the tomato and onion.
Season with lime juice, pepper and salt. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy hot rolls
directions: Soften yeast cakes in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add sugar.
Mix boiling water with the 1/2 cup sugar, salt and shortening.
Let stand until lukewarm; mix with the yeast mixture.
Now, stir in the 2 beaten eggs.
Add flour slowly, beating constantly to make a smooth dough that will not stick to your fingers.
Let rise, then knead.
Roll out and cut into rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° to 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Cut steak in 1-inch cubes.
Mix soup and wine together.
Add meat and mushrooms.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Serve over noodles and rice.

title: shrimp paste
directions: Combine ingredients with softened cream cheese.
Serve with crackers.
I prefer Waverly wafers.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Combine and mix 15 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with cream cheese icing.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce pieces in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle peas over lettuce;
scatter
green
pepper on top, then do the same with the onion.
Spread
mayonnaise
over
all; then sprinkle Parmesan cheese and bacon on top.
Chill several hours for the flavors to mingle.

title: baked beans with ground beef
directions: Cook meat in skillet until done and drain well.
Add all ingredients to meat and bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Cook onions,
peppers,	garlic and celery until tender; simmer in	butter.
Add soups, parsley, green onions, crawfish and pimento, chopped; heat thoroughly.	Stir in rice and bread crumbs. Turn
into
3 quart casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and bake at 350°
for	30
minutes
or until bread crumbs are brown.

title: baked fudge pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix the flour, granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons of cocoa, baking powder and salt in ungreased baking pan (9 x 9-inch).
Mix milk, oil and vanilla with fork until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Spread mixture evenly in pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup of cocoa.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Top is crusty and pudding on bottom is thickened.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in buttered casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Spread over chicken.
Mix cracker crumbs with butter and sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: old-time down home hickory ridge good ol' boys pit barbecue sauce(grandpaw heber's)
directions: Slow cook onion in oil until soft.
If onion burns, throw the whole mess out and start over.
Add remaining stuff, bring to a boil, then simmer for at least 30 minutes.

title: creamy vegetable soup
directions: Combine broth and water in a large kettle and bring to a boil. Add vegetables and cook until just tender.
Strain, reserving liquid.
Set vegetables aside.
Return liquid to kettle. Blend butter into flour.
Add a little of the liquid to make a smooth paste.
Stir into liquid and cook briefly.
Reduce heat; add cheese, milk and pepper.
Beat a little of the liquid into the yolks and add to soup.
Return vegetables to soup and heat but do not boil.
Sprinkle parsley on top of soup in bowls.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning; set aside. Spread bean dip into serving dish.
Top and layer with avocado, sour cream mixture, green onion, tomatoes, olives and shredded cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: artichoke bread
directions: Let mixture (all but bread) set overnight.
Roll out dough into rectangle.
Put mixture down center.
Fold shut and keep shut with toothpicks.
Brush top with olive oil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: surprise butterscotch cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread in a 9 x 15-inch pan. Sprinkle with butterscotch chips and a few nuts.
Bake per directions on cake mix box.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook beef and onion until brown. Add remaining ingredients. Heat thoroughly. Serve in toasted buns.

title: easy cherry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese.
Then add Dream Whip. Mix well. Pour in pie shell.
Put pie filling on top.
Chill 3 hours before serving.

title: tuna chowder
directions: Peel and dice potatoes. Boil potatoes, onions, parsley flakes, salt and pepper until tender.
Flake tuna from can with fork.
Add canned corn and tomato soup; cook another 5 minutes. Add cheese and stir until well mixed.
Really great with hot biscuits.

title: rocky road
directions: In a saucepan, combine chocolate pieces, condensed milk and margarine. Heat over low heat until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Add onion juice and stir thoroughly.
Add oil slowly, beating constantly until thickened.
Add poppy seeds and beat again (medium speed).
Store in refrigerator, but not close to freezer unit.
Good on fresh fruit or salad.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with bananas.
Add nuts.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cut beef into bite size pieces.
Chop onions, green peppers and celery.
Roll beef in flour, salt and pepper.
Saute beef in frying pan until browned.

title: spinach bread
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine.
Add squeezed spinach; saute.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Cut French bread lengthwise.
Spread softened margarine on both sides.
Spread spinach on one side.
Close.
Wrap in foil.
Heat until hot at 350°.
You can serve as open-faced or sandwich style pieces.

title: apple bread
directions: Dissolve baking soda in the sour milk.
Beat shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add sour milk mixture and vanilla.
Add the flour mixture.
Add the chopped apples.
Put in greased and floured loaf pans.
Before baking, top with Crumble Mixture.

title: crispy southern fried chicken
directions: Beat together egg, water and 1/4 cup Crisco oil.
Add sugar, salt and flour; mix until smooth.
Dip chicken one piece at a time into batter.
Fry for about 25 to 30 minutes in an uncovered skillet which contains 1/2 inch of oil, heated to 365° to 375°. Turn chicken often for even browning.

title: mixed vegetables casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and celery together for about 10 minutes in small amount of water; drain.
Add onion and water chestnuts.
Mix soup and mayonnaise and add 1/2 cup cheese to the vegetables. Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on and then top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook peppers in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix ground beef, bread or cracker crumbs, salt, pepper and chopped onion.
Add tomato soup.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture.
Stand upright in small baking dish.
Pour over remaining soup, diluted with 1/2 soup can water.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes and uncovered 15 minutes longer at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Roll sausage into small balls.
Fry balls at medium heat, turning frequently, until brown on all sides.
Put apple butter in a chafing dish and heat.
Add warm sausage to apple butter in chafing dish and allow to stand for 30 minutes or more.
Serve hot with toothpicks.
Yields 50.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Brown ground beef, then drain.
Add all other ingredients. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin chews
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine flour, soda, salt and oats. Mix well and set aside.
Blend sugars; add butter and mix to form a grainy paste.
Add honey, then vanilla and eggs.
Mix until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture, raisins and walnuts.
Do not overmix.
Drop by rounded tablespoons on ungreased sheet 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake 22 to 24 minutes or until light brown. Immediately transfer cookies with a spatula to a cool flat surface.

title: deep-dish beef pie
directions: Spray a large skillet with nonstick coating.
Preheat over medium-high heat.
Brown half the meat in skillet.
Remove.
Add oil.
Brown remaining meat.
Return all meat to skillet.
Stir in onion, celery, carrots, turnip, tomato juice, thyme, salt, pepper and 1 cup water.
Cover and simmer 50 to 60 minutes or till meat is nearly tender.
Combine flour and 2 tbsp. water.
Stir into skillet mixture.
Cook and stir till thickened and bubbly.
Stir in green beans.
Spoon into a 1 1/2 qt. casserole.

title: bean casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.
Can be doubled for big crowd.

title: freezing dough bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add honey, molasses and melted butter.
(Traditionally, you would add salt at this point. However, we've left the salt out of this recipe because American diets tend to contain unhealthfully high amounts of it.
Unsalted bread has a different flavor from what may be accustomed to, a flavor some have come to prefer.
If saltless bread is unappetizing to you, however, why not try cutting the amount you would ordinarily bake with in half?)
Add powdered milk and flour, a few cups at a time, until you get a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown meat and onions in a large pan.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for about 1 hour.
Serve on buns.

title: honey-citrus ice tea
directions: Place tea bags in a teapot; add boiling water.
Cover and steep for 3 minutes; discard tea bags.
Pour tea into a pitcher. Peel and section two oranges and one lemon; add to tea.
Stir in the orange juice, lemon juice and honey.
Cover and refrigerate for 6 hours or overnight.
Cut remaining orange and lemon into slices; freeze.
Just before serving, strain and discard fruit from tea.
Stir in ginger ale.
Serve with frozen fruit slices.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place in 9x13 baking dish.
Peel and slice potatoes and onions and layer over pork chops.
Slice green pepper in rings and arrange on top.
Mix soup with milk until blended and pour over casserole.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350 for 1 hour.
Serves:

title: grape leaf pickles
directions: Mix the sugar, salt, vinegar and water in a saucepan.
Begin to heat solution over medium heat.
While solution is heating, add enough cucumbers to fill a quart jar to the solution.
Keep in until cucumbers just turn color.
Pack in jar; pour solution over them and seal.

title: pie crust
directions: Pour all ingredients in pie pan.
Using fork, mix together. With fingers, shape in ball, then start pressing dough flat and up on side to form shell.

title: potato cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Blend in potatoes and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa and soda; add alternating with milk, blending well after each addition.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
You may ice or serve with Cool Whip.

title: fried chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Combine flour, paprika, salt and pepper in a plastic bag.
Combine garlic powder, oregano and cayenne in shaker.
Heat shortening to 375° in a heavy deep skillet.
Beat eggs in water.
Shake chicken a few pieces at a time in flour mixture to coat.
Dip in egg mixture, then shake again in flour mixture.
Fry for 10 minutes, skin side down, turn and fry for 20 minutes, turning occasionally.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with spice mix.

title: quick sticky buns
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch square cake pan.
Stir in sugar, cinnamon, corn syrup, nuts and raisins.
Place biscuit dough on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until biscuits are well done. Let stand for 5 minutes, then place on serving plate and remove pan.

title: short ribs
directions: Heat oil in a Dutch oven.
Add short ribs and brown on all sides.
Add seasonings, onion and hot water.
Cover and simmer on low flame for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat. Blend flour and cold water; stir into liquid in pan and continue to cook, stirring, until gravy boils and thickens.
Season gravy to taste.
Pour over ribs and serve at once.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave on High chocolate and vanilla bits for 2 minutes. Stir until smooth.
Add marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Stir and pour on greased pizza pan.
Add cherries and coconut as toppings.
Great for a kid's party.

title: sweet buttery beans
directions: Cook beans as directed on package; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
(Cooked fresh or canned beans can also be used.)

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Blend beans and juice in a food processor until smooth.
In a separate bowl, mix sugar, eggs, melted butter and vanilla.
Add blended beans, coconut and nuts.
Pour into the unbaked pie shells. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Yields 3 pies.

title: cherry delight
directions: Spread pie filling in a long baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over this as it comes from the box.
Drizzle melted margarine over this and top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: golden fry batter
directions: Mix flour and vegetable oil together.
Add egg, milk and salt. Use egg beater and beat all together.
Dip onion in flour first, then batter.
Use on onion rings, mushrooms, frog legs, etc.

title: microwave chocolate cheese pie
directions: Place cream cheese in medium baking dish.
Microwave at power High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until cream cheese softens.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer until blended.
Set aside.
Melt chocolate for 2 1/2 to 4 minutes or until chocolate is smooth when stirred.
Add cream cheese and sour cream.
Beat at low speed until smooth.
Pour into prepared crust.
Microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes or until center is slightly set.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Chill for 6 hours or until set.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: el rancho casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Cover; cook slowly until macaroni is done.
Add cheese cubes.
Turn heat off; let set for few minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: breakfast before
directions: Butter (or use cooking spray) a 12 x 8-inch dish.
Spread bread cubes in bottom of dish.
Brown sausage and drain well.
Spread evenly over bread.
Mix milk, eggs, salt and mustard until well blended.
Pour over sausage.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll out dough.
Put out cookies. Sprinkle granulated sugar onto each cookie and press in lightly. Bake 8 to 9 minutes in 400° oven.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spoon flour into cup; level off.
In a large bowl, combine the first 3 ingredients.
Blend at low until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Press 2 3/4 cups crumb mixture into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Cook chicken in salt water until tender.

Pour off 2 cups of broth and set aside. Debone meat and cut in bite-size pieces. Place evenly in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish. Prepare stuffing according to package directions, using the broth for water.
Place stuffing over chicken.
Mix the soup and milk and spread over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Serves 6 or 8 people.

title: asparagus make ahead
directions: Beat eggs, milk, onion, asparagus, melted butter, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and add a dash of paprika, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until completely set.
This can be made ahead and baked at serving time.

title: grits 'n cheese bake
directions: Stir grits slowly into salted, boiling water in a large boiler. Cook over low heat about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in Cheddar cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, butter, milk and eggs. Continue cooking over low heat until Cheddar cheese is melted.

title: swiss ring around
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl combine parsley, onion, mustard, margarine and lemon juice; blend well.
Add cheese, broccoli and meat; mix lightly; set aside.
On greased cookie sheet arrange crescent roll triangles, points toward the outside.
Bases of triangle should form a circle with bases overlapping.
The center of circle should be about 3 inches in diameter.
Spoon mixture evenly over base.
Fold points of triangles over filling and tuck under bases.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake crust (rolled real thin).

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off fat.
Add Worcestershire sauce, chili and tomatoes or catsup.
Add beans.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Mix the flour, cornmeal, buttermilk, egg and oil.
Stir until blended.
Spread on top of bean mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425°.
Good with slaw or tossed salad.

title: broiled chicken deluxe(good low-fat recipe)
directions: Place chicken in pan in a single layer and rub with lemon juice, saving some for the meal.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Spray
5 cup mold with non-stick cooking spray.
Combine all ingredients; stir until well blended.
Pour into mold and freeze for several hours or overnight.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Mix as you would for pie crust.
Put in a greased pizza pan. Bake for 8 minutes at 425°.
If pizza pan is large, make a double batch of the crust and use at least 1 3/4 of the mixture.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Soften cheese with cranberry sauce and pineapple. Blend sugar and salad dressing with whipped cream.
Mix with cheese mixture until smooth.
Add nuts and freeze into squares before serving. You can use a refrigerator tray for freezing or 1 1/2-quart dish.

title: russian tea
directions: Heat to simmering in electric cooker-fryer.

title: grandma's dessert
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: health sandwich
directions: Toss the first 6 ingredients and place on bread.
Combine the honey, lemon juice and yogurt; blend until smooth.
Spoon the dressing over the vegetables and sprinkle alfalfa sprouts on top.

title: pudding bar
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts together, pat in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Let cool.

title: diane's raisin pie
directions: Cover raisins with water.
Add sugar and cook until boiling. Mix flour and margarine (will be lumpy).
Add to hot raisin mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour in unbaked crust.
Top with another crust.
Bake at 350°.

title: pumpkin-nut bread
directions: Blend sugar, oleo and eggs, one at a time.
Add pumpkin, flour and spices.
Beat together.
Add nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in 2 greased and floured bread pans.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cut fruit in small pieces, mixing in pecans, then flour.
Coat well; shake through sifter to remove excess flour.
Set aside; cream oleo and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute, then add flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add fruit and pecans; mix with hand (there will be just enough batter to hold together).
Drop by tablespoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Batter will keep well for weeks.
Cookies are better after they set awhile.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup strawberry juice for icing.
Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: english muffins and black olives
directions: Mix together and spread on English muffins. Cut in quarters and broil until bubbles and
light brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; remove from broth.
Add noodles to broth and cook.
Drain.
Mix chicken, noodles, soup and sour cream together. Place in casserole dish.
Top with bread squares.
Add 2 tablespoons butter on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: autumn soup
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain if needed.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and cover and simmer about 30 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Add fine egg noodles.
Add 1/4 teaspoon oregano and thyme.

title: praline cake
directions: Combine brown sugar, sour cream, 2 tablespoons butter and cornstarch in 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and set aside.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Pour into a square casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Mix cornflakes and butter.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until crisp.

title: veg dip
directions: Mix well together.
Pour back into carton and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with mixed raw vegetables.

title: easy low-fat dream cake
directions: Slice angel food cake into 3 layer sections.
Mix instant pudding according to box instructions.
Fold yogurt into pudding. Spread yogurt mixture on first layer, then top with a cake layer. Continue this until each layer is frosted.
"Ice" entire cake with Cool Whip.
Top with sliced fresh fruit.
(Strawberries and peaches are my family's two favorites.)
Chill until ready to serve.

title: southern sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pie shell) well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: chocolate mint brownies
directions: Mix sugar, salt, syrup, vanilla, nuts, 1/2 cup butter, eggs and flour.
Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
(If you get lazy like I sometimes do, use a boxed brownie mix.)

title: the king's chicken
directions: Remove chicken skin.
Wash chicken; pat dry and place in a Ziploc bag.
Pour Italian dressing over chicken and marinate in refrigerator for a few hours.
Place chicken and dressing in a shallow casserole dish.
Place sliced onion on top of chicken. Sprinkle with paprika to taste.
Bake, covered, for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt earlie's sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add salt and spices.
Mix thoroughly. Add cream and stir.
Add the mashed potatoes and mix well. Turn into pie shell and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: one egg rolls
directions: Cream the sugar and Crisco. Add 1 cup water with yeast; dissolve.
Mix salt, flour, egg and other 1/2 cup water.

Stir all together to make a stiff dough, then knead about 30 times or more. Shape in muffin pan and refrigerate for about 3 to 4 hours. Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking and let rise in warm place. Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: kugel
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; add already cooked and partially cooled noodles, preserves, raisins, cottage cheese, sour cream, oleo and cinnamon.
Mix it all well.
Put it in a 9 x 12-inch pan (pregreased).
Sprinkle a little cinnamon on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until lightly brown on top.

title: delicious baked chicken(easy! easy! easy!)
directions: Mix soup and sour cream. Add salt and pepper to taste.
After rinsing the dried beef with water to remove excess salt, layer dried beef above and below chicken.
Pour soup/sour cream mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: pan fried cajun shrimp
directions: Saute garlic cloves in butter until soft.
Press with fork to release garlic juices.
Remove garlic clove pieces.
Stir shrimp into bowl of barbecue sauce, cayenne pepper and black pepper, coating all shrimp.
Place in frying pan of garlic butter and simmer until shrimp are done.
Approximate time:
5 minutes to cook shrimp.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Add the sugar first to the cream cheese and beat in one egg at a time.
Beat until smooth, then pour over the crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
