Remove from oven and pour over it 1 can of cherry or blueberry pie filling mix.
Top with whipped cream if you wish.

title: christmas cranberry mold
directions: Put jello in cold and hot water, sugar, salt and whole cranberry sauce.
Let set until cool, then add all other ingredients.
Place it in a mold and let chill 4 hours.
Place mold in warm water until it moves from its sides, then place on lettuce on a platter.

title: sauteed zucchini and carrots
directions: Saute carrots in butter over medium heat 4 minutes. Add onion; cook 1 minute. Add zucchini and next 3 ingredients; cover and cook 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp-tender. Garnish if desired. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: hearty ribs and beans
directions: Place ribs in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add 1/4 cup water. Cover tightly and cook in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Remove to absorbent paper.
Pour off cooking liquid and reserve.
Combine tomato sauce, onion soup mix, brown sugar, prepared mustard and hot sauce in small saucepan and cook slowly 10 minutes.
Remove excess fat from cooking liquid, add enough water to remaining liquid to make 1 cup.
Stir into sauce mixture.
Combine white and red beans, celery, and red or green pepper and mixture in a baking dish.
May lay ribs on top or cut into bite-size pieces and mix in with beans and sauce.
Cover tightly and bake in 350° oven 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sweet onion casserole
directions: Place onion rings in greased 2-quart casserole.
Melt butter and add flour, milk, salt, paprika and Lea & Perrins.
Cook until thick.
Stir in cheese and green chilies.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Pour over onions.
Sprinkle Bac*Os or crumbled bacon on top.
Cover and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes at 425°.

title: mary's baked cheese cake
directions: Beat
cottage
cheese
and cream cheese together for 10 minutes or until really smooth.
Add sugar and eggs.
Also add juice
from
lemon and vanilla.
Melt margarine and cool.
Add cornstarch and flour to mixture.
Blend in sour cream.
Grease and flour
spring-form
pan.
Bake
1 hour at 350°.
Leave in oven to
cool for 2 hours or more.
Take knife and cut around edges before
releasing sides of pan.
Upset onto cake plate. Any pie filling can be used for topping as you wish.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain beans slightly.
Brown ground beef with onion; drain. Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old south cucumber lime pickles
directions: Soak clean cucumbers in water and lime mixture in crockery or enamel ware for 12 hours or overnight.
Do not use aluminum ware.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Brown the sausage; drain.
Add oregano and garlic.
On a greased baking sheet flatten 10 biscuits to 4-inch circles with floured custard cup.
Leave rim.
Fill with tomato paste and sausage.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage with knife.
Cook cabbage in pot with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon margarine until tender.
Make a white sauce by combining 2 cups milk, 2 tablespoons margarine, 2 tablespoons self-rising flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir constantly as sauce begins to thicken.
Drain cabbage and mix with sauce.
In a casserole dish alternately layer cabbage mixture and cheese ending with cheese on top.
Sprinkle saltines on top.
Place in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Add pumpkin.
Stir in ingredients. Spray 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet with Baker's Joy.
Spread on cookie sheet and sprinkle with 1 cup chopped pecans.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle large cloth with powdered sugar.
Turn cake out on cloth and roll up to cool.
May put in freezer for 30 minutes.

title: corn bread sticks
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add egg, lard and buttermilk.
Beat well.
Pour into 2 greased corn stick pans. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 14 corn sticks.

title: pumpkin spice bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a large mixing bowl, combine pumpkin, sugar, water, vegetable oil, and eggs.
Beat until well mixed.
Measure the flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, nutmeg and ground cloves into a separate bowl.
Stir, slowly and add the dry ingredients to the pumpkin mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Grease and flour 2 9 x 5 inch loaf pans.
Evenly divide the batter between the two pans.
Bake for 60 - 70 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 - 15 minutes.
Then remove from pans by inverting them onto a rack, and tapping the bottoms.
Slice and serve plain, buttered, or with cream cheese.

title: autumn fruitcake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: amaretto
directions: Combine water and sugar in a saucepan.
Make a simple syrup by boiling for about 5 minutes. Cool completely then add brandy, vodka and almond extract.

title: ranch hand muffins
directions: On a griddle or skillet, heat butter.
Saute ham until heated and beginning to get crispy.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Turn heat to low.
Cover with lid.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need 9-inch diameter clay flower pot and hand spade (for serving).

title: betty valillo's chicken divan
directions: Saute chicken pieces in margarine until partially cooked (approximately 1 to 2 minutes each side).
Lay chicken pieces in bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle thawed broccoli over chicken.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Combine mayonnaise and cream; pour over cucumber and onion slices until all are covered.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and add sugar gradually and continue creaming until sugar and shortening are well blended.
Add molasses and egg and beat well.
Sift the dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture; beat until smooth.
Roll in small balls or drop mixture from a teaspoon about 2 inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: diabetic date cake
directions: Cook raisins or dates with 2 cups water until water is absorbed; cool.
Add 1 cup applesauce, eggs, oil and sweetener. Mix.
Add 2 cups flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla. Blend well.
Grease loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs. Slice in half long ways. Scoop the yolk out and smash with fork. Stir in mayonnaise, mustard and salt and pepper. Spoon mix into egg whites.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar.
Add	milk.
Sift
flour with baking powder and add nuts.
Add to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites until peaks form.
Fold in.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 30	to
35	minutes.
Frost
with a chocolate boiled frosting.

title: tony's shrimp jambalaya supreme
directions: Saute onions in butter for 5 minutes until clear.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add garlic, celery, bell pepper, parsley, thyme and cloves.
Cook 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in rice. Season to taste and simmer 30 minutes, stirring often.

title: quickie cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter and pour in 8-inch glass pan.
Mix together sugar, flour and baking powder.
Gradually add milk, stirring to blend.
Pour in with melted butter.
Stir a few times, then add cherries and rake them through batter with a fork. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: peanut butter clouds
directions: In a small bowl, beat egg white and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in sugar, beating until stiff peaks form. With a rubber spatula or spoon, work in peanut butter.
Drop mixture from teaspoon 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 18 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly before removing from sheet.
Yields 12.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Put about 1 cup water in bottom of pan.

title: quail leg hors d'oeuvres
directions: In medium bowl, put quail legs and honey.
Stir to coat legs. Mix all dry ingredients together in large plastic bag.
Add quail legs and shake to coat.
Saute legs on medium heat until golden brown.
Watch carefully so as not to burn.
Drain on paper towels and serve warm as an appetizer with a dipping sauce.

title: chicken tosca
directions: Dredge each piece of chicken in plain flour, then dip in the egg, half and half and garlic that have been beaten together in a shallow bowl.
Coat with the flour, Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes, that have been combined in a shallow pan.
Salt each piece lightly before turning to coat second side.
Saute in mixture of butter and vegetable oil until golden and done.
Meat should be moist and juicy inside and crispy outside.

title: chicken salad
directions: Lightly mix all ingredients.
Toss with mayo until evenly coated.
Chill.
Serve in lettuce cups.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix butter and both corns.
Put in glass cake pan.
Sprinkle Jiffy corn mix on top and put slices of butter on it. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Chop bananas and apple and add to fruit cocktail.
Add remaining ingredients and mix. Garnish with cherries and pecans.

title: enchiladas
directions: In a large skillet, cook ground beef until crumbly.
Drain fat.
(Include onion when cooking the beef.)
Open the can of enchilada sauce and pour approximately 1/2 cup of sauce into beef; mix well.
In a small skillet, heat 1/2 cup of oil until warm. Cook the corn tortillas slightly on each side until they are soft. In a large baking dish place a tortilla inside.
Spoon into the tortilla a couple of tablespoons of meat.
Add a bit of cheese and roll the tortilla until the bottom is toward the bottom of the baking dish.
Continue until you run out of meat or tortillas. Pour the rest of the enchilada sauce on the top of the enchiladas and pour the remaining cheese on top of that.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with rice or beans. Garnish with fresh olives.

title: heavenly onions
directions: Simmer onions in butter until tender.
Put in 1-quart casserole and top with cheese and pepper.
Heat soup, milk and soy sauce until blended; pour over onions.
Mix with knife.
Cover with bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: golden cream soup
directions: Combine first six ingredients in 2 or 3 quart pan.
Mix. Cover and simmer for 15 - 20 minutes.
Add flour to milk and mix until smooth.
Add to vegetables.
Cook until desired thickness. Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Serves 3 - 4.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time. Mix in flour and vanilla. Add 7-Up; mix well. Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts, dates, cranberries and orange rind.
Combine eggs, buttermilk and oil. Add to flour mixture.
Stir until blended.
Pour into well greased tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove to plate; place on wide pan and spoon marinade over warm cake until it is absorbed into cake.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry
rice
in
saucepan
using a small amount of oil or olive oil.
Add onion and fry. Add tomatoes. Cover with water and simmer until
water
is
gone and rice is fluffy.
Do not stir.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix juice from fruit cocktail and pineapple in pistachio pudding, then mix in rest of ingredients.
Cool and enjoy.

title: baked apples
directions: Cut pared apples into eighths and place in buttered casserole. Pour liquid over apples and sprinkle with brown sugar evenly. Dot with margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon and lightly with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple wine
directions: Use 3 to 5 gallon plastic container or stone crock.
Place in chopped or thinly sliced apples, stems removed.
(Do not use blender or food processor, will cause cloudy wine.) Add water and yeast; stir well.
Cover container with clean dish towel and secure with huge rubber band or string.

title: beef and potato loaf
directions: Arrange evenly in a greased 2-quart dish, 4 cups thinly sliced, raw potatoes and 1 teaspoon cut-up onion, sprinkled with 1 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and 1 teaspoon parsley flakes.
Spread meat mixture evenly over potatoes.
Decorate top with more catsup, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven (moderate) 1 hour, until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks and jam. Sift the flour.
Measure; add baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg and sift 3 times.
Dissolve soda in the sour milk.
Add flour and milk alternately to the mixture, beating well.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites and bake in 2 layer pans about 25 minutes in moderate oven (350°).

title: oyster crackers
directions: Combine dressing mix and oil (start with 1/2 cup and add more if needed).
Add dill weed, garlic powder, and lemon pepper.
Pour over crackers.
Stir to coat.
Place on a cookie sheet in a warm oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Store in a airtight container.

title: whole wheat pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in warm mixing bowl. Add salt, olive oil and all-purpose flour.
Mix 2 minutes.
Continue to mix and add whole wheat flour, 1/2 cup at a time, until dough clings to the mixer.
Knead dough for a few minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place, free from draft, until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down.
Let rest 10 minutes. Divide dough in half.
(Dough can be wrapped in plastic wrap and refrigerated overnight or frozen for later use.)

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: Put sugar, milk and butter in pan and boil for 9 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add chocolate and marshmallows; stir until completely melted.
Add peanut butter (use less if you want; only a hint of taste; I use crunchy peanut butter).
Pour into greased pan.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: divine date-nut loaf
directions: Beat together the eggs, sugar and oil. Add the dry ingredients and mix together well. Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan (9 x 5 x 2-inch) and place in a cold oven. Turn on the oven to 300° and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until cake is firm in the middle. Let cool completely. Remove from pan and slice with a very sharp knife or wrap and freeze for slicing and serving later. Makes a 3 pound loaf.

title: creamy chicken bake
directions: Place one slice of Swiss cheese on each piece of chicken. Stir together soup and wine.
Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top and drizzle with melted margarine or butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Original recipe taken from Niagara Deanery ECW Cookbook.

title: sherried chicken and artichokes
directions: Melt butter in skillet (that has a cover).
Salt and pepper chicken pieces; then place in pan and brown.
Leave chicken in pan and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until juices are low.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Arrange whole crackers in bottom of an 11 x 9-inch pan. Combine in saucepan the milk, sugar, flour, butter and beaten egg. Cook over medium heat, stirring, until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add the nuts, coconut, crumbs and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon over crackers in pan.
Top with whole graham crackers.

title: magnificent meatballs
directions: Mix together beef, 1 cup tomatoes, bread crumbs, egg, salt, pepper, oregano and onion.
Form into 12 good sized (about 3-inch diameter) meatballs.
Wrap each with bacon slice, overlapping bacon carefully.
Place meatballs in large, flat baking dish (roasting pan is handy) so that overlapped bacon is on bottom. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Remove from oven and pour off bacon fat.

title: cranberry apple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add next 3 ingredients; mix well.
Pour into serving dish.
Refrigerate until set.

title: crazy berry blue pie
directions: Put water and gelatin into small saucepan.
Place over direct heat; stir until dissolved or mixture is clear.
In medium bowl, combine condensed milk and lemon juice.
Stir in gelatin mixture. Fold in sour cream.
Mix in 1 1/2 cups of pie filling.
Turn into crust.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Garnish top of pie with remaining pie filling.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Grease 9 or 10 inch tube pan.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Beat yolks until light.
Add sugar gradually, pineapple juice and vanilla.
Then add flour, salt and baking powder.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: oven easy chicken
directions: Shake chicken in paper bag with seasoned flour.
Melt butter or margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken skin side down. Bake uncovered at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add apples and raisins last. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: grandma's potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in water until tender.
Mash and add remaining ingredients.
Simple, yet delicious!

title: harvest potatoes with herbs
directions: In a small bowl combine seasonings.
Place 2 tablespoons in a nonstick skillet.
Arrange a third of the potato slices in a circular pattern in skillet.
Sprinkle about 1/4 of the seasonings, 4 tablespoons butter and 2 teaspoons onion.
Repeat layers twice. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Invert onto serving platter to unmold potatoes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peach delight
directions: Grind peaches and cherries.
Add pineapple and sugar.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Put into jars and seal.

title: chocolate ice cream cake roll
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line a 15 1/2 x 10 1/4 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with aluminum foil or waxed paper; grease.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.

title: ice cream
directions: This is the best ice cream I've every made.
This is served at all our reunions.

title: meat and potato dinner
directions: Layer ingredients in order given. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: squash paddies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl; cover and let stand.
Drain thoroughly. (Hint:
To drain, you will need to press down on ingredients because squash has a lot of water content.) Add flour and eggs.
Stir well.
Melt margarine in a large skillet over medium heat.
Drop squash mixture by tablespoon into hot margarine.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.
Serves 6-8.

title: louisiana dirty rice
directions: Brown flour in oil until it is a deep red-brown, stirring constantly to prevent burning.
Add onions, celery, green pepper and garlic; cook until tender.
Stir in beef, pork, giblets and seasonings.
Continue cooking until meat loses it's color.
Blend in broth; cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Stir in rice and onion tops.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Mixture should be slightly moist. Makes 6 servings.
Rice can be placed in baking dish and served later, 350° for 30 minutes, covered.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, brown sugar, molasses, salt, soda and shortening.
Add eggs slowly and cream in mixture. Add flour, ginger and cinnamon using slowest speed on mixture. Roll dough to a 1/4-inch for small gingerbread or 1/2-inch for large gingerbread.
Cut cookies out and put on baking sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen gingerbread men.

title: cheese french bread
directions: Cut bread lengthwise in half.
Mix all ingredients together. Spread on both halves of bread.
Bake in 200° oven for 20 minutes or until browned.
Slice and serve.

title: quick tomato soup
directions: Mix flour and butter in saucepan.
Add chicken stock, stirring constantly.
Add tomato juice and canned tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Cook rice in another saucepan.
Drain and add to soup.
Garnish with grated cheese.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook the pie shell.
Place the strawberries in the shell.
In a saucepan, combine the flour, jello, sugar, water and salt.
Cook until it gets thick, about 15 minutes.
Pour over berries.
Chill pie overnight or several hours.
Cover with Cool Whip and serve.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place potatoes on 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown, stirring once.
Mix dressing, bacon, eggs, onions, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Add potatoes and mix lightly.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini delight
directions: Cook and drain the ground beef.
Slice and parboil the zucchini.
Cook the potatoes.
In a 2 1/2-quart greased casserole dish, layer the beef, zucchini squash, potatoes and cheese.
Mix the soup and milk.
Pour over.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: famous oatmeal cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour water over oatmeal and let stand 20 minutes.
Cream sugars, shortening and eggs.
Add oatmeal.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Test for doneness with toothpick.
Cool.
Top with topping as follows.

title: onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large plastic bag and shake until well coated.
Empty bag into an ungreased 9 x 13 pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until tender.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown turkey; add green pepper and onion.
Reduce heat; cover and cook until peppers are tender.
Add beans, tomatoes and chili mix.
Simmer 10 minutes and serve.

title: sweet potato stuffed squash
directions: Cut squash in half from bottom end to stem end.
Remove seeds. Sprinkle with salt.
Place squash, cut side down, in shallow pan; add boiling water to depth of 1/2 inch to pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until tender.
Pour off water.
Turn squash upside down.

title: tofu burgers(no dairy, low-fat)
directions: Mash tofu and combine all ingredients; mix well.
Knead 2 or 3 minutes.
Moisten hands and form 4 large burgers.
Cook slowly on both sides until golden, either in nonstick baking dish in the oven or in a lightly oiled skillet on top of the range.
Serve in a bun with fixings, on half bun, topped with a large slice of tomato, or as an entree with vegetables.
Yields 4 servings.

title: artichoke pizza
directions: Unroll dough, without tearing; press into 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until cooked through.

title: ice cream from instant pudding
directions: Mix pudding per directions on box.
Add eggs, sugar, half and half and vanilla.
Pour into ice cream maker.
Add whole milk to finish.

title: crowd size potato salad
directions: Cook and dice potatoes and eggs.
Mix with mayonnaise and onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 125 people.

title: deer chili
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight in water 2-inches above beans. Cook in same water until done.
Do not drain.
Add tomatoes and simmer for 5 minutes.
Saute green peppers in salad oil for 5 minutes.
Add onions and cook until tender, stirring often.
Add garlic and parsley.
Melt butter in large skillet and saute meat for 15 minutes.
Add meat to onion mixture and stir in chili powder and cook 10 minutes.
Add this to beans and the spices. Simmer covered for 1 hour.
Cook uncovered for 30 minutes.
For even better chili, simmer very slowly all day.
Add a little water as needed.

title: luke's soup(a kid's recipe)
directions: Cook soup according to package directions.
Add tuna and cook 1 more minute.
Serve with grated cheese or croutons.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and milk, mixing until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill. Serve in cabbage shell with vegetable dippers.

title: chinese chewies
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend well.
Put in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Remove from pan while hot.

title: chicken casserole #1
directions: Pat stuffing into greased casserole.
Top with shredded chicken.
Add crumbled broccoli.
Top with chicken and celery soup.
Top with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: yummy fruit salad pie
directions: Drain juice from cherries.
Add enough water to make 2 cups of liquid.
Add cornstarch; cook until clear.
Remove from fire.
Add Jell-O, sugar, pineapple, cherries, food coloring, bananas and nuts.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix at high speed the sugar and oil. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat for 1 minute after each egg. Add sifted ingredients and mix with a large spoon.
Add cut up apples, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan 1 hour at 350°.
Have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: yeast dinner rolls
directions: Bring milk to boil; add Crisco.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm.
Put sugar, yeast and salt in large mixing bowl.
Add lukewarm water.
After mixture is dissolved, add warm milk and eggs plus half of the flour.
Beat well with mixer.
Add rest of flour and mix well with dough hook on mixer.
Cover and place in the refrigerator overnight.
Shape into 24 balls and place in a greased 11 x 14-inch pan.
Let rise until soft to touch.
I use RapidRise yeast for best results.
This is a rich sweet dough that is great for pecan or cinnamon rolls.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix marinade and pour over carrots, onion and peppers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain before serving.
Serves 12.
Keeps well refrigerated in covered container.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in electric mixer for 2 minutes. Bake in lightly greased loaf pans for 50 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: lentil soup
directions: Saute garlic, celery and onion in the margarine.
Add carrots, juice, potatoes and rice.
Rinse lentils and mix all together. Bring to a boil.
Stir, cover and simmer until tender.
If desired, stir in corn for last 20 minutes.

title: i hate to bake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread the pineapple with juice in pan.
Spread the cherry pie filling next. Sprinkle the dry cake mix over the filling.
Sprinkle the nuts next.
Cut up the butter; scatter over the top.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Brown chopped onion.
Add ground meat and continue browning. Add rice, parsley, salt, pepper, oregano and basil; stir to blend. Add canned tomatoes with liquid.
Simmer until rice is partially cooked (10 minutes); stir constantly.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Wash peppers; slice off tops (reserve for covers). Remove seeds.
Place peppers into boiling water and parboil for 5 to 10 minutes; cool.
Stuff peppers with filling and place in a deep pot.
Add boiling water to cover peppers 3/4 way up.
Add tablespoon of butter; cover and cook over low heat until rice is tender, about 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in buttermilk and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and sugar; cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Make a swell in center of mixture; add reserved yeast mixture; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured work surface, and knead lightly 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, free of drafts, for 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until biscuits are lightly browned.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken.
Use broth to cook spaghetti until tender.
Mix pepper, French fried onion rings, pimento and soups with spaghetti. Add chicken and some of the cheese, leaving some for the top.
Add mushrooms and celery.
Put in baking dish and cover with cheese. Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ranch style goulash
directions: Season with garlic powder and crushed red pepper.
Heat and eat.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water.
Scald the milk. Add sugar, shortening and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast and eggs. Stir in flour.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Stir down.
Let rise a second time. Roll out and cut with cutter.
Fold over.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: mom's melt-in-your-mouth pot roast
directions: In heavy pot*, melt shortening. Coat meat lightly with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown meat on each side in hot fat over medium-high heat. Sprinkle onion over top.
Pour in chili sauce and 2 to 3 cups water to cover.
Simmer, covered, at least 3 hours.

title: apricot smokies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a skillet and heat on high until hot.

title: special scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix together well. Bake in a 3-quart casserole dish or baking pan for 45 minutes to 1 hour (uncovered). Stir every 15 minutes.

title: pasta salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and puree until smooth.
Add and toss with pasta and veggies.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add oatmeal to water and set aside to cool.
Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.

Add oatmeal and beat until fluffy. Add dry ingredients sifted together. Add flavoring. Bake in greased shallow pan, 13 x 8-inches, 45 minutes to 1 hour. Add topping to cake and brown for about 10 minutes. This is a moist cake and keeps well. Serves 20.

title: sweet potatoes - apricot
directions: Cut potatoes in half; place as one layer in greased 10 x 6-inch glass dish.
Drain apricots, keep 1 cup syrup.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon, orange peel and syrup.
Cook, stirring, on medium heat until it boils.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add apricots, butter and nuts.
Pour over potatoes. Bake, uncovered, about 25 minutes at 375°.

title: hamburger biscuit casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread in cake pans.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick until smooth.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese; bake 5 to 10 more minutes.

title: pumpkin bread(makes 3 loaves)
directions: Combine all ingredients together (except raisins and nuts) with a mixer until well blended.
Then add nuts and raisins.
Pour into 3 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix together potatoes, egg, onion and flour.
Drop a spoonful in a skillet of hot grease.
Pat with a spoon to flatten.
Brown on both sides.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook all vegetables in the water in a large, covered saucepan for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Add seasonings.
Add milk to the flour and blend.
Then add to vegetable mixture and cook to thicken.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: "she" crab soup
directions: Saute onion in butter (do not brown).
Add flour, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to onion in butter.
Add half and half and cook over low heat. Stir constantly until thick. Remove from heat and add the crabmeat and wine.
Top with pat of butter when ready to serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate shell peanuts
directions: Combine peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Chill and prepare dough.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg and vanilla.
Beat well and blend in flour, cocoa and salt.
Shape into balls, using half teaspoonful for each.
Flatten each ball and place 1/4 teaspoonful of peanut butter mixture in center.
Shape dough around filling, pressing to seal.
Pinch ends and centers of cookies to form "peanuts".
Bake at 325° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Roll warm cookies in powdered sugar.

title: hot cheese squares
directions: Soften cheese and margarine to room temperature.
Add remaining ingredients and beat in electric mixer until light and fluffy; will resemble whipped cream.
Stack 3 slices of bread, removing crust.
Spread cheese mixture between slices and cut into fourths.
Three slices of bread will make four small squares. Frost squares with cheese, leaving bottoms uniced.
Freeze on a cookie sheet and then remove to storage container.
Bake frozen on a cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve immediately.
If you do not wish to freeze, chill in refrigerator overnight before baking.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Fry pork chops without grease until brown.
Mix other ingredients.
Place pork chops on top in a covered casserole. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper.
Cook macaroni according to directions.
Add all ingredients to meat.
Pour in ungreased casserole dish.
Top with slices of cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ranch style baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef in oleo in skillet.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: oven barbecued chicken wings
directions: Cut each chicken wing at joints to make 3 pieces; discard tips. Cut off and discard excess skin.
Place chicken in shallow glass or plastic dish.
Prepare Hoisin-Ginger Marinade.
Pour marinade over chicken; turn to coat with marinade.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Prepare Dream Whip.
Add cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix until smooth and pour over cooled crust.
Spread pie filling over top of cheese mixture and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Store leftovers in refrigerator.

title: brandicot chicken(makes 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to moderate 375°.
Stir together the cornstarch and soy sauce in a saucepan.
Stir in apricot preserves, sugar, vinegar, garlic, ginger and pepper.
Cook over medium to high heat until thick and bubbly (2 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in orange juice and brandy.
Place chicken, skin side down, in a shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Pour sauce over top.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken pieces; baste with sauce.
Bake additional 30 minutes, or until tender.

title: mashed sweet potatoes(yields 6 servings)
directions: Peel the sweet potatoes and cook them in boiling water until they are soft.
Pour off any water that is left.
Put the sugar and unsalted butter in with the sweet potatoes and mash them all together either with a potato masher or a spoon.

title: ants on a log
directions: Spread the peanut butter on the celery.
Place 4 to 5 raisins in a row on top of the peanut butter.
Serves 4 with 106 calories each.

title: nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a loaf bread pan.
Sift flour, then measure 3 cups.
Add the other dry ingredients to the flour. Beat the egg in a mixing bowl.
Add the sour milk and sugar.
Mix. Add the dry ingredients into the egg mixture.
Add the nuts. Beat until well mixed.
Pour into a greased bread pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Variation:
Add dates, raisins or bananas.

title: banana squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl beat butter and sugar with mixer until creamy.
Beat in egg, vanilla and banana.
